1042 /// If we have a clamp pattern like max (min X, 42), 41 -- where the output
1043 /// can only be one of two possible constant values -- turn that into a select
1044 /// of constants.
1045 static Instruction *foldClampRangeOfTwo(IntrinsicInst *II,
1046  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
1047  Value *I0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *I1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1048  Value *X;
1049  const APInt *C0, *C1;
1050  if (!match(I1, m_APInt(C1)) || !I0->hasOneUse())
1051  return nullptr;
1052 
1053  CmpInst::Predicate Pred = CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE;
1054  switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
1055  case Intrinsic::smax:
1056  if (match(I0, m_SMin(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0))) && *C0 == *C1 + 1)
1057  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
1058  break;
1059  case Intrinsic::smin:
1060  if (match(I0, m_SMax(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0))) && *C1 == *C0 + 1)
1061  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
1062  break;
1063  case Intrinsic::umax:
1064  if (match(I0, m_UMin(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0))) && *C0 == *C1 + 1)
1065  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
1066  break;
1067  case Intrinsic::umin:
1068  if (match(I0, m_UMax(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0))) && *C1 == *C0 + 1)
1069  Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
1070  break;
1071  default:
1072  llvm_unreachable("Expected min/max intrinsic");
1073  }
1074  if (Pred == CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE)
1075  return nullptr;
1076 
1077  // max (min X, 42), 41 --> X > 41 ? 42 : 41
1078  // min (max X, 42), 43 --> X < 43 ? 42 : 43
1079  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, X, I1);
1080  return SelectInst::Create(Cmp, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), *C0), I1);
1081 }
1082 
1083 /// If this min/max has a constant operand and an operand that is a matching
1084 /// min/max with a constant operand, constant-fold the 2 constant operands.
1085 static Instruction *reassociateMinMaxWithConstants(IntrinsicInst *II) {
1086  Intrinsic::ID MinMaxID = II->getIntrinsicID();
1087  auto *LHS = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(II->getArgOperand(0));
1088  if (!LHS || LHS->getIntrinsicID() != MinMaxID)
1089  return nullptr;
1090 
1091  Constant *C0, *C1;
1092  if (!match(LHS->getArgOperand(1), m_ImmConstant(C0)) ||
1093  !match(II->getArgOperand(1), m_ImmConstant(C1)))
1094  return nullptr;
1095 
1096  // max (max X, C0), C1 --> max X, (max C0, C1) --> max X, NewC
1097  ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = MinMaxIntrinsic::getPredicate(MinMaxID);
1098  Constant *CondC = ConstantExpr::getICmp(Pred, C0, C1);
1099  Constant *NewC = ConstantExpr::getSelect(CondC, C0, C1);
1100 
1101  Module *Mod = II->getModule();
1102  Function *MinMax = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, MinMaxID, II->getType());
1103  return CallInst::Create(MinMax, {LHS->getArgOperand(0), NewC});
1104 }
1105 
1106 /// If this min/max has a matching min/max operand with a constant, try to push
1107 /// the constant operand into this instruction. This can enable more folds.
1108 static Instruction *
1109 reassociateMinMaxWithConstantInOperand(IntrinsicInst *II,
1110  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
1111  // Match and capture a min/max operand candidate.
1112  Value *X, *Y;
1113  Constant *C;
1114  Instruction *Inner;
1115  if (!match(II, m_c_MaxOrMin(m_OneUse(m_CombineAnd(
1116  m_Instruction(Inner),
1117  m_MaxOrMin(m_Value(X), m_ImmConstant(C)))),
1118  m_Value(Y))))
1119  return nullptr;
1120 
1121  // The inner op must match. Check for constants to avoid infinite loops.
1122  Intrinsic::ID MinMaxID = II->getIntrinsicID();
1123  auto *InnerMM = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Inner);
1124  if (!InnerMM || InnerMM->getIntrinsicID() != MinMaxID ||
1125  match(X, m_ImmConstant()) || match(Y, m_ImmConstant()))
1126  return nullptr;
1127 
1128  // max (max X, C), Y --> max (max X, Y), C
1129  Function *MinMax =
1130  Intrinsic::getDeclaration(II->getModule(), MinMaxID, II->getType());
1131  Value *NewInner = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(MinMaxID, X, Y);
1132  NewInner->takeName(Inner);
1133  return CallInst::Create(MinMax, {NewInner, C});
1134 }
1135 
1136 /// Reduce a sequence of min/max intrinsics with a common operand.
1137 static Instruction *factorizeMinMaxTree(IntrinsicInst *II) {
1138  // Match 3 of the same min/max ops. Example: umin(umin(), umin()).
1139  auto *LHS = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(II->getArgOperand(0));
1140  auto *RHS = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(II->getArgOperand(1));
1141  Intrinsic::ID MinMaxID = II->getIntrinsicID();
1142  if (!LHS || !RHS || LHS->getIntrinsicID() != MinMaxID ||
1143  RHS->getIntrinsicID() != MinMaxID ||
1144  (!LHS->hasOneUse() && !RHS->hasOneUse()))
1145  return nullptr;
1146 
1147  Value *A = LHS->getArgOperand(0);
1148  Value *B = LHS->getArgOperand(1);
1149  Value *C = RHS->getArgOperand(0);
1150  Value *D = RHS->getArgOperand(1);
1151 
1152  // Look for a common operand.
1153  Value *MinMaxOp = nullptr;
1154  Value *ThirdOp = nullptr;
1155  if (LHS->hasOneUse()) {
1156  // If the LHS is only used in this chain and the RHS is used outside of it,
1157  // reuse the RHS min/max because that will eliminate the LHS.
1158  if (D == A || C == A) {
1159  // min(min(a, b), min(c, a)) --> min(min(c, a), b)
1160  // min(min(a, b), min(a, d)) --> min(min(a, d), b)
1161  MinMaxOp = RHS;
1162  ThirdOp = B;
1163  } else if (D == B || C == B) {
1164  // min(min(a, b), min(c, b)) --> min(min(c, b), a)
1165  // min(min(a, b), min(b, d)) --> min(min(b, d), a)
1166  MinMaxOp = RHS;
1167  ThirdOp = A;
1168  }
1169  } else {
1170  assert(RHS->hasOneUse() && "Expected one-use operand");
1171  // Reuse the LHS. This will eliminate the RHS.
1172  if (D == A || D == B) {
1173  // min(min(a, b), min(c, a)) --> min(min(a, b), c)
1174  // min(min(a, b), min(c, b)) --> min(min(a, b), c)
1175  MinMaxOp = LHS;
1176  ThirdOp = C;
1177  } else if (C == A || C == B) {
1178  // min(min(a, b), min(b, d)) --> min(min(a, b), d)
1179  // min(min(a, b), min(c, b)) --> min(min(a, b), d)
1180  MinMaxOp = LHS;
1181  ThirdOp = D;
1182  }
1183  }
1184 
1185  if (!MinMaxOp || !ThirdOp)
1186  return nullptr;
1187 
1188  Module *Mod = II->getModule();
1189  Function *MinMax = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, MinMaxID, II->getType());
1190  return CallInst::Create(MinMax, { MinMaxOp, ThirdOp });
1191 }
1192 
1193 /// If all arguments of the intrinsic are unary shuffles with the same mask,
1194 /// try to shuffle after the intrinsic.
1195 static Instruction *
1196 foldShuffledIntrinsicOperands(IntrinsicInst *II,
1197  InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
1198  // TODO: This should be extended to handle other intrinsics like fshl, ctpop,
1199  // etc. Use llvm::isTriviallyVectorizable() and related to determine
1200  // which intrinsics are safe to shuffle?
1201  switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
1202  case Intrinsic::smax:
1203  case Intrinsic::smin:
1204  case Intrinsic::umax:
1205  case Intrinsic::umin:
1206  case Intrinsic::fma:
1207  case Intrinsic::fshl:
1208  case Intrinsic::fshr:
1209  break;
1210  default:
1211  return nullptr;
1212  }
1213 
1214  Value *X;
1215  ArrayRef<int> Mask;
1216  if (!match(II->getArgOperand(0),
1217  m_Shuffle(m_Value(X), m_Undef(), m_Mask(Mask))))
1218  return nullptr;
1219 
1220  // At least 1 operand must have 1 use because we are creating 2 instructions.
1221  if (none_of(II->args(), [](Value *V) { return V->hasOneUse(); }))
1222  return nullptr;
1223 
1224  // See if all arguments are shuffled with the same mask.
1225  SmallVector<Value *, 4> NewArgs(II->arg_size());
1226  NewArgs[0] = X;
1227  Type *SrcTy = X->getType();
1228  for (unsigned i = 1, e = II->arg_size(); i != e; ++i) {
1229  if (!match(II->getArgOperand(i),
1230  m_Shuffle(m_Value(X), m_Undef(), m_SpecificMask(Mask))) ||
1231  X->getType() != SrcTy)
1232  return nullptr;
1233  NewArgs[i] = X;
1234  }
1235 
1236  // intrinsic (shuf X, M), (shuf Y, M), ... --> shuf (intrinsic X, Y, ...), M
1237  Instruction *FPI = isa<FPMathOperator>(II) ? II : nullptr;
1238  Value *NewIntrinsic =
1239  Builder.CreateIntrinsic(II->getIntrinsicID(), SrcTy, NewArgs, FPI);
1240  return new ShuffleVectorInst(NewIntrinsic, Mask);
1241 }
1242 
1243 /// CallInst simplification. This mostly only handles folding of intrinsic
1244 /// instructions. For normal calls, it allows visitCallBase to do the heavy
1245 /// lifting.
1246 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::visitCallInst(CallInst &CI) {
1247  // Don't try to simplify calls without uses. It will not do anything useful,
1248  // but will result in the following folds being skipped.
1249  if (!CI.use_empty())
1250  if (Value *V = simplifyCall(&CI, SQ.getWithInstruction(&CI)))
1251  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, V);
1252 
1253  if (Value *FreedOp = getFreedOperand(&CI, &TLI))
1254  return visitFree(CI, FreedOp);
1255 
1256  // If the caller function (i.e. us, the function that contains this CallInst)
1257  // is nounwind, mark the call as nounwind, even if the callee isn't.
1258  if (CI.getFunction()->doesNotThrow() && !CI.doesNotThrow()) {
1259  CI.setDoesNotThrow();
1260  return &CI;
1261  }
1262 
1263  IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(&CI);
1264  if (!II) return visitCallBase(CI);
1265 
1266  // For atomic unordered mem intrinsics if len is not a positive or
1267  // not a multiple of element size then behavior is undefined.
1268  if (auto *AMI = dyn_cast<AtomicMemIntrinsic>(II))
1269  if (ConstantInt *NumBytes = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(AMI->getLength()))
1270  if (NumBytes->getSExtValue() < 0 ||
1271  (NumBytes->getZExtValue() % AMI->getElementSizeInBytes() != 0)) {
1272  CreateNonTerminatorUnreachable(AMI);
1273  assert(AMI->getType()->isVoidTy() &&
1274  "non void atomic unordered mem intrinsic");
1275  return eraseInstFromFunction(*AMI);
1276  }
1277 
1278  // Intrinsics cannot occur in an invoke or a callbr, so handle them here
1279  // instead of in visitCallBase.
1280  if (auto *MI = dyn_cast<AnyMemIntrinsic>(II)) {
1281  bool Changed = false;
1282 
1283  // memmove/cpy/set of zero bytes is a noop.
1284  if (Constant *NumBytes = dyn_cast<Constant>(MI->getLength())) {
1285  if (NumBytes->isNullValue())
1286  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
1287  }
1288 
1289  // No other transformations apply to volatile transfers.
1290  if (auto *M = dyn_cast<MemIntrinsic>(MI))
1291  if (M->isVolatile())
1292  return nullptr;
1293 
1294  // If we have a memmove and the source operation is a constant global,
1295  // then the source and dest pointers can't alias, so we can change this
1296  // into a call to memcpy.
1297  if (auto *MMI = dyn_cast<AnyMemMoveInst>(MI)) {
1298  if (GlobalVariable *GVSrc = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(MMI->getSource()))
1299  if (GVSrc->isConstant()) {
1300  Module *M = CI.getModule();
1301  Intrinsic::ID MemCpyID =
1302  isa<AtomicMemMoveInst>(MMI)
1303  ? Intrinsic::memcpy_element_unordered_atomic
1304  : Intrinsic::memcpy;
1305  Type *Tys[3] = { CI.getArgOperand(0)->getType(),
1306  CI.getArgOperand(1)->getType(),
1307  CI.getArgOperand(2)->getType() };
1308  CI.setCalledFunction(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, MemCpyID, Tys));
1309  Changed = true;
1310  }
1311  }
1312 
1313  if (AnyMemTransferInst *MTI = dyn_cast<AnyMemTransferInst>(MI)) {
1314  // memmove(x,x,size) -> noop.
1315  if (MTI->getSource() == MTI->getDest())
1316  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
1317  }
1318 
1319  // If we can determine a pointer alignment that is bigger than currently
1320  // set, update the alignment.
1321  if (auto *MTI = dyn_cast<AnyMemTransferInst>(MI)) {
1322  if (Instruction *I = SimplifyAnyMemTransfer(MTI))
1323  return I;
1324  } else if (auto *MSI = dyn_cast<AnyMemSetInst>(MI)) {
1325  if (Instruction *I = SimplifyAnyMemSet(MSI))
1326  return I;
1327  }
1328 
1329  if (Changed) return II;
1330  }
1331 
1332  // For fixed width vector result intrinsics, use the generic demanded vector
1333  // support.
1334  if (auto *IIFVTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(II->getType())) {
1335  auto VWidth = IIFVTy->getNumElements();
1336  APInt UndefElts(VWidth, 0);
1337  APInt AllOnesEltMask(APInt::getAllOnes(VWidth));
1338  if (Value *V = SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(II, AllOnesEltMask, UndefElts)) {
1339  if (V != II)
1340  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, V);
1341  return II;
1342  }
1343  }
1344 
1345  if (II->isCommutative()) {
1346  if (CallInst *NewCall = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
1347  return NewCall;
1348  }
1349 
1350  // Unused constrained FP intrinsic calls may have declared side effect, which
1351  // prevents it from being removed. In some cases however the side effect is
1352  // actually absent. To detect this case, call SimplifyConstrainedFPCall. If it
1353  // returns a replacement, the call may be removed.
1354  if (CI.use_empty() && isa<ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(CI)) {
1355  if (simplifyConstrainedFPCall(&CI, SQ.getWithInstruction(&CI)))
1356  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
1357  }
1358 
1359  Intrinsic::ID IID = II->getIntrinsicID();
1360  switch (IID) {
1361  case Intrinsic::objectsize:
1362  if (Value *V = lowerObjectSizeCall(II, DL, &TLI, AA, /*MustSucceed=*/false))
1363  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, V);
1364  return nullptr;
1365  case Intrinsic::abs: {
1366  Value *IIOperand = II->getArgOperand(0);
1367  bool IntMinIsPoison = cast<Constant>(II->getArgOperand(1))->isOneValue();
1368 
1369  // abs(-x) -> abs(x)
1370  // TODO: Copy nsw if it was present on the neg?
1371  Value *X;
1372  if (match(IIOperand, m_Neg(m_Value(X))))
1373  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
1374  if (match(IIOperand, m_Select(m_Value(), m_Value(X), m_Neg(m_Deferred(X)))))
1375  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
1376  if (match(IIOperand, m_Select(m_Value(), m_Neg(m_Value(X)), m_Deferred(X))))
1377  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
1378 
1379  if (std::optional<bool> Sign = getKnownSign(IIOperand, II, DL, &AC, &DT)) {
1380  // abs(x) -> x if x >= 0
1381  if (!*Sign)
1382  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, IIOperand);
1383 
1384  // abs(x) -> -x if x < 0
1385  if (IntMinIsPoison)
1386  return BinaryOperator::CreateNSWNeg(IIOperand);
1387  return BinaryOperator::CreateNeg(IIOperand);
1388  }
1389 
1390  // abs (sext X) --> zext (abs X*)
1391  // Clear the IsIntMin (nsw) bit on the abs to allow narrowing.
1392  if (match(IIOperand, m_OneUse(m_SExt(m_Value(X))))) {
1393  Value *NarrowAbs =
1394  Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::abs, X, Builder.getFalse());
1395  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::ZExt, NarrowAbs, II->getType());
1396  }
1397 
1398  // Match a complicated way to check if a number is odd/even:
1399  // abs (srem X, 2) --> and X, 1
1400  const APInt *C;
1401  if (match(IIOperand, m_SRem(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C))) && *C == 2)
1402  return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(X, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), 1));
1403 
1404  break;
1405  }
1406  case Intrinsic::umin: {
1407  Value *I0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *I1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1408  // umin(x, 1) == zext(x != 0)
1409  if (match(I1, m_One())) {
1410  assert(II->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() != 1 &&
1411  "Expected simplify of umin with max constant");
1412  Value *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(I0->getType());
1413  Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(I0, Zero);
1414  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::ZExt, Cmp, II->getType());
1415  }
1416  [[fallthrough]];
1417  }
1418  case Intrinsic::umax: {
1419  Value *I0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *I1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1420  Value *X, *Y;
1421  if (match(I0, m_ZExt(m_Value(X))) && match(I1, m_ZExt(m_Value(Y))) &&
1422  (I0->hasOneUse() || I1->hasOneUse()) && X->getType() == Y->getType()) {
1423  Value *NarrowMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, X, Y);
1424  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::ZExt, NarrowMaxMin, II->getType());
1425  }
1426  Constant *C;
1427  if (match(I0, m_ZExt(m_Value(X))) && match(I1, m_Constant(C)) &&
1428  I0->hasOneUse()) {
1429  Constant *NarrowC = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, X->getType());
1430  if (ConstantExpr::getZExt(NarrowC, II->getType()) == C) {
1431  Value *NarrowMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, X, NarrowC);
1432  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::ZExt, NarrowMaxMin, II->getType());
1433  }
1434  }
1435  // If both operands of unsigned min/max are sign-extended, it is still ok
1436  // to narrow the operation.
1437  [[fallthrough]];
1438  }
1439  case Intrinsic::smax:
1440  case Intrinsic::smin: {
1441  Value *I0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *I1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1442  Value *X, *Y;
1443  if (match(I0, m_SExt(m_Value(X))) && match(I1, m_SExt(m_Value(Y))) &&
1444  (I0->hasOneUse() || I1->hasOneUse()) && X->getType() == Y->getType()) {
1445  Value *NarrowMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, X, Y);
1446  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::SExt, NarrowMaxMin, II->getType());
1447  }
1448 
1449  Constant *C;
1450  if (match(I0, m_SExt(m_Value(X))) && match(I1, m_Constant(C)) &&
1451  I0->hasOneUse()) {
1452  Constant *NarrowC = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, X->getType());
1453  if (ConstantExpr::getSExt(NarrowC, II->getType()) == C) {
1454  Value *NarrowMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, X, NarrowC);
1455  return CastInst::Create(Instruction::SExt, NarrowMaxMin, II->getType());
1456  }
1457  }
1458 
1459  if (IID == Intrinsic::smax || IID == Intrinsic::smin) {
1460  // smax (neg nsw X), (neg nsw Y) --> neg nsw (smin X, Y)
1461  // smin (neg nsw X), (neg nsw Y) --> neg nsw (smax X, Y)
1462  // TODO: Canonicalize neg after min/max if I1 is constant.
1463  if (match(I0, m_NSWNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(I1, m_NSWNeg(m_Value(Y))) &&
1464  (I0->hasOneUse() || I1->hasOneUse())) {
1465  Intrinsic::ID InvID = getInverseMinMaxIntrinsic(IID);
1466  Value *InvMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(InvID, X, Y);
1467  return BinaryOperator::CreateNSWNeg(InvMaxMin);
1468  }
1469  }
1470 
1471  // If we can eliminate ~A and Y is free to invert:
1472  // max ~A, Y --> ~(min A, ~Y)
1473  //
1474  // Examples:
1475  // max ~A, ~Y --> ~(min A, Y)
1476  // max ~A, C --> ~(min A, ~C)
1477  // max ~A, (max ~Y, ~Z) --> ~min( A, (min Y, Z))
1478  auto moveNotAfterMinMax = [&](Value *X, Value *Y) -> Instruction * {
1479  Value *A;
1480  if (match(X, m_OneUse(m_Not(m_Value(A)))) &&
1481  !isFreeToInvert(A, A->hasOneUse()) &&
1482  isFreeToInvert(Y, Y->hasOneUse())) {
1483  Value *NotY = Builder.CreateNot(Y);
1484  Intrinsic::ID InvID = getInverseMinMaxIntrinsic(IID);
1485  Value *InvMaxMin = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(InvID, A, NotY);
1486  return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(InvMaxMin);
1487  }
1488  return nullptr;
1489  };
1490 
1491  if (Instruction *I = moveNotAfterMinMax(I0, I1))
1492  return I;
1493  if (Instruction *I = moveNotAfterMinMax(I1, I0))
1494  return I;
1495 
1496  if (Instruction *I = moveAddAfterMinMax(II, Builder))
1497  return I;
1498 
1499  // smax(X, -X) --> abs(X)
1500  // smin(X, -X) --> -abs(X)
1501  // umax(X, -X) --> -abs(X)
1502  // umin(X, -X) --> abs(X)
1503  if (isKnownNegation(I0, I1)) {
1504  // We can choose either operand as the input to abs(), but if we can
1505  // eliminate the only use of a value, that's better for subsequent
1506  // transforms/analysis.
1507  if (I0->hasOneUse() && !I1->hasOneUse())
1508  std::swap(I0, I1);
1509 
1510  // This is some variant of abs(). See if we can propagate 'nsw' to the abs
1511  // operation and potentially its negation.
1512  bool IntMinIsPoison = isKnownNegation(I0, I1, /* NeedNSW */ true);
1513  Value *Abs = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
1514  Intrinsic::abs, I0,
1515  ConstantInt::getBool(II->getContext(), IntMinIsPoison));
1516 
1517  // We don't have a "nabs" intrinsic, so negate if needed based on the
1518  // max/min operation.
1519  if (IID == Intrinsic::smin || IID == Intrinsic::umax)
1520  Abs = Builder.CreateNeg(Abs, "nabs", /* NUW */ false, IntMinIsPoison);
1521  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Abs);
1522  }
1523 
1524  if (Instruction *Sel = foldClampRangeOfTwo(II, Builder))
1525  return Sel;
1526 
1527  if (Instruction *SAdd = matchSAddSubSat(*II))
1528  return SAdd;
1529 
1530  if (match(I1, m_ImmConstant()))
1531  if (auto *Sel = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I0))
1532  if (Instruction *R = FoldOpIntoSelect(*II, Sel))
1533  return R;
1534 
1535  if (Instruction *NewMinMax = reassociateMinMaxWithConstants(II))
1536  return NewMinMax;
1537 
1538  if (Instruction *R = reassociateMinMaxWithConstantInOperand(II, Builder))
1539  return R;
1540 
1541  if (Instruction *NewMinMax = factorizeMinMaxTree(II))
1542  return NewMinMax;
1543 
1544  break;
1545  }
1546  case Intrinsic::bitreverse: {
1547  // bitrev (zext i1 X to ?) --> X ? SignBitC : 0
1548  Value *X;
1549  if (match(II->getArgOperand(0), m_ZExt(m_Value(X))) &&
1550  X->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1)) {
1551  Type *Ty = II->getType();
1552  APInt SignBit = APInt::getSignMask(Ty->getScalarSizeInBits());
1553  return SelectInst::Create(X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, SignBit),
1554  ConstantInt::getNullValue(Ty));
1555  }
1556  break;
1557  }
1558  case Intrinsic::bswap: {
1559  Value *IIOperand = II->getArgOperand(0);
1560 
1561  // Try to canonicalize bswap-of-logical-shift-by-8-bit-multiple as
1562  // inverse-shift-of-bswap:
1563  // bswap (shl X, Y) --> lshr (bswap X), Y
1564  // bswap (lshr X, Y) --> shl (bswap X), Y
1565  Value *X, *Y;
1566  if (match(IIOperand, m_OneUse(m_LogicalShift(m_Value(X), m_Value(Y))))) {
1567  // The transform allows undef vector elements, so try a constant match
1568  // first. If knownbits can handle that case, that clause could be removed.
1569  unsigned BitWidth = IIOperand->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
1570  const APInt *C;
1571  if ((match(Y, m_APIntAllowUndef(C)) && (*C & 7) == 0) ||
1572  MaskedValueIsZero(Y, APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, 3))) {
1573  Value *NewSwap = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::bswap, X);
1574  BinaryOperator::BinaryOps InverseShift =
1575  cast<BinaryOperator>(IIOperand)->getOpcode() == Instruction::Shl
1576  ? Instruction::LShr
1577  : Instruction::Shl;
1578  return BinaryOperator::Create(InverseShift, NewSwap, Y);
1579  }
1580  }
1581 
1582  KnownBits Known = computeKnownBits(IIOperand, 0, II);
1583  uint64_t LZ = alignDown(Known.countMinLeadingZeros(), 8);
1584  uint64_t TZ = alignDown(Known.countMinTrailingZeros(), 8);
1585  unsigned BW = Known.getBitWidth();
1586 
1587  // bswap(x) -> shift(x) if x has exactly one "active byte"
1588  if (BW - LZ - TZ == 8) {
1589  assert(LZ != TZ && "active byte cannot be in the middle");
1590  if (LZ > TZ) // -> shl(x) if the "active byte" is in the low part of x
1591  return BinaryOperator::CreateNUWShl(
1592  IIOperand, ConstantInt::get(IIOperand->getType(), LZ - TZ));
1593  // -> lshr(x) if the "active byte" is in the high part of x
1594  return BinaryOperator::CreateExactLShr(
1595  IIOperand, ConstantInt::get(IIOperand->getType(), TZ - LZ));
1596  }
1597 
1598  // bswap(trunc(bswap(x))) -> trunc(lshr(x, c))
1599  if (match(IIOperand, m_Trunc(m_BSwap(m_Value(X))))) {
1600  unsigned C = X->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits() - BW;
1601  Value *CV = ConstantInt::get(X->getType(), C);
1602  Value *V = Builder.CreateLShr(X, CV);
1603  return new TruncInst(V, IIOperand->getType());
1604  }
1605  break;
1606  }
1607  case Intrinsic::masked_load:
1608  if (Value *SimplifiedMaskedOp = simplifyMaskedLoad(*II))
1609  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, SimplifiedMaskedOp);
1610  break;
1611  case Intrinsic::masked_store:
1612  return simplifyMaskedStore(*II);
1613  case Intrinsic::masked_gather:
1614  return simplifyMaskedGather(*II);
1615  case Intrinsic::masked_scatter:
1616  return simplifyMaskedScatter(*II);
1617  case Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group:
1618  case Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group:
1619  if (auto *SkippedBarrier = simplifyInvariantGroupIntrinsic(*II, *this))
1620  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, SkippedBarrier);
1621  break;
1622  case Intrinsic::powi:
1623  if (ConstantInt *Power = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(1))) {
1624  // 0 and 1 are handled in instsimplify
1625  // powi(x, -1) -> 1/x
1626  if (Power->isMinusOne())
1627  return BinaryOperator::CreateFDivFMF(ConstantFP::get(CI.getType(), 1.0),
1628  II->getArgOperand(0), II);
1629  // powi(x, 2) -> x*x
1630  if (Power->equalsInt(2))
1631  return BinaryOperator::CreateFMulFMF(II->getArgOperand(0),
1632  II->getArgOperand(0), II);
1633 
1634  if (!Power->getValue()[0]) {
1635  Value *X;
1636  // If power is even:
1637  // powi(-x, p) -> powi(x, p)
1638  // powi(fabs(x), p) -> powi(x, p)
1639  // powi(copysign(x, y), p) -> powi(x, p)
1640  if (match(II->getArgOperand(0), m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) ||
1641  match(II->getArgOperand(0), m_FAbs(m_Value(X))) ||
1642  match(II->getArgOperand(0),
1643  m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(X), m_Value())))
1644  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
1645  }
1646  }
1647  break;
1648 
1649  case Intrinsic::cttz:
1650  case Intrinsic::ctlz:
1651  if (auto *I = foldCttzCtlz(*II, *this))
1652  return I;
1653  break;
1654 
1655  case Intrinsic::ctpop:
1656  if (auto *I = foldCtpop(*II, *this))
1657  return I;
1658  break;
1659 
1660  case Intrinsic::fshl:
1661  case Intrinsic::fshr: {
1662  Value *Op0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *Op1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1663  Type *Ty = II->getType();
1664  unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
1665  Constant *ShAmtC;
1666  if (match(II->getArgOperand(2), m_ImmConstant(ShAmtC))) {
1667  // Canonicalize a shift amount constant operand to modulo the bit-width.
1668  Constant *WidthC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, BitWidth);
1669  Constant *ModuloC =
1670  ConstantFoldBinaryOpOperands(Instruction::URem, ShAmtC, WidthC, DL);
1671  if (!ModuloC)
1672  return nullptr;
1673  if (ModuloC != ShAmtC)
1674  return replaceOperand(*II, 2, ModuloC);
1675 
1676  assert(ConstantExpr::getICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT, WidthC, ShAmtC) ==
1677  ConstantInt::getTrue(CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(Ty)) &&
1678  "Shift amount expected to be modulo bitwidth");
1679 
1680  // Canonicalize funnel shift right by constant to funnel shift left. This
1681  // is not entirely arbitrary. For historical reasons, the backend may
1682  // recognize rotate left patterns but miss rotate right patterns.
1683  if (IID == Intrinsic::fshr) {
1684  // fshr X, Y, C --> fshl X, Y, (BitWidth - C)
1685  Constant *LeftShiftC = ConstantExpr::getSub(WidthC, ShAmtC);
1686  Module *Mod = II->getModule();
1687  Function *Fshl = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::fshl, Ty);
1688  return CallInst::Create(Fshl, { Op0, Op1, LeftShiftC });
1689  }
1690  assert(IID == Intrinsic::fshl &&
1691  "All funnel shifts by simple constants should go left");
1692 
1693  // fshl(X, 0, C) --> shl X, C
1694  // fshl(X, undef, C) --> shl X, C
1695  if (match(Op1, m_ZeroInt()) || match(Op1, m_Undef()))
1696  return BinaryOperator::CreateShl(Op0, ShAmtC);
1697 
1698  // fshl(0, X, C) --> lshr X, (BW-C)
1699  // fshl(undef, X, C) --> lshr X, (BW-C)
1700  if (match(Op0, m_ZeroInt()) || match(Op0, m_Undef()))
1701  return BinaryOperator::CreateLShr(Op1,
1702  ConstantExpr::getSub(WidthC, ShAmtC));
1703 
1704  // fshl i16 X, X, 8 --> bswap i16 X (reduce to more-specific form)
1705  if (Op0 == Op1 && BitWidth == 16 && match(ShAmtC, m_SpecificInt(8))) {
1706  Module *Mod = II->getModule();
1707  Function *Bswap = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::bswap, Ty);
1708  return CallInst::Create(Bswap, { Op0 });
1709  }
1710  }
1711 
1712  // Left or right might be masked.
1713  if (SimplifyDemandedInstructionBits(*II))
1714  return &CI;
1715 
1716  // The shift amount (operand 2) of a funnel shift is modulo the bitwidth,
1717  // so only the low bits of the shift amount are demanded if the bitwidth is
1718  // a power-of-2.
1719  if (!isPowerOf2_32(BitWidth))
1720  break;
1721  APInt Op2Demanded = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, Log2_32_Ceil(BitWidth));
1722  KnownBits Op2Known(BitWidth);
1723  if (SimplifyDemandedBits(II, 2, Op2Demanded, Op2Known))
1724  return &CI;
1725  break;
1726  }
1727  case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
1728  case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow: {
1729  if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
1730  return I;
1731 
1732  // Given 2 constant operands whose sum does not overflow:
1733  // uaddo (X +nuw C0), C1 -> uaddo X, C0 + C1
1734  // saddo (X +nsw C0), C1 -> saddo X, C0 + C1
1735  Value *X;
1736  const APInt *C0, *C1;
1737  Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
1738  Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1739  bool IsSigned = IID == Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow;
1740  bool HasNWAdd = IsSigned ? match(Arg0, m_NSWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0)))
1741  : match(Arg0, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0)));
1742  if (HasNWAdd && match(Arg1, m_APInt(C1))) {
1743  bool Overflow;
1744  APInt NewC =
1745  IsSigned ? C1->sadd_ov(*C0, Overflow) : C1->uadd_ov(*C0, Overflow);
1746  if (!Overflow)
1747  return replaceInstUsesWith(
1748  *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
1749  IID, X, ConstantInt::get(Arg1->getType(), NewC)));
1750  }
1751  break;
1752  }
1753 
1754  case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
1755  case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
1756  case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
1757  if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
1758  return I;
1759  break;
1760 
1761  case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow: {
1762  if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
1763  return I;
1764 
1765  Constant *C;
1766  Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
1767  Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1768  // Given a constant C that is not the minimum signed value
1769  // for an integer of a given bit width:
1770  //
1771  // ssubo X, C -> saddo X, -C
1772  if (match(Arg1, m_Constant(C)) && C->isNotMinSignedValue()) {
1773  Value *NegVal = ConstantExpr::getNeg(C);
1774  // Build a saddo call that is equivalent to the discovered
1775  // ssubo call.
1776  return replaceInstUsesWith(
1777  *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow,
1778  Arg0, NegVal));
1779  }
1780 
1781  break;
1782  }
1783 
1784  case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
1785  case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
1786  case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
1787  case Intrinsic::ssub_sat: {
1788  SaturatingInst *SI = cast<SaturatingInst>(II);
1789  Type *Ty = SI->getType();
1790  Value *Arg0 = SI->getLHS();
1791  Value *Arg1 = SI->getRHS();
1792 
1793  // Make use of known overflow information.
1794  OverflowResult OR = computeOverflow(SI->getBinaryOp(), SI->isSigned(),
1795  Arg0, Arg1, SI);
1796  switch (OR) {
1797  case OverflowResult::MayOverflow:
1798  break;
1799  case OverflowResult::NeverOverflows:
1800  if (SI->isSigned())
1801  return BinaryOperator::CreateNSW(SI->getBinaryOp(), Arg0, Arg1);
1802  else
1803  return BinaryOperator::CreateNUW(SI->getBinaryOp(), Arg0, Arg1);
1804  case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsLow: {
1805  unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
1806  APInt Min = APSInt::getMinValue(BitWidth, !SI->isSigned());
1807  return replaceInstUsesWith(*SI, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Min));
1808  }
1809  case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsHigh: {
1810  unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
1811  APInt Max = APSInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth, !SI->isSigned());
1812  return replaceInstUsesWith(*SI, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Max));
1813  }
1814  }
1815 
1816  // ssub.sat(X, C) -> sadd.sat(X, -C) if C != MIN
1817  Constant *C;
1818  if (IID == Intrinsic::ssub_sat && match(Arg1, m_Constant(C)) &&
1819  C->isNotMinSignedValue()) {
1820  Value *NegVal = ConstantExpr::getNeg(C);
1821  return replaceInstUsesWith(
1822  *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
1823  Intrinsic::sadd_sat, Arg0, NegVal));
1824  }
1825 
1826  // sat(sat(X + Val2) + Val) -> sat(X + (Val+Val2))
1827  // sat(sat(X - Val2) - Val) -> sat(X - (Val+Val2))
1828  // if Val and Val2 have the same sign
1829  if (auto *Other = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Arg0)) {
1830  Value *X;
1831  const APInt *Val, *Val2;
1832  APInt NewVal;
1833  bool IsUnsigned =
1834  IID == Intrinsic::uadd_sat || IID == Intrinsic::usub_sat;
1835  if (Other->getIntrinsicID() == IID &&
1836  match(Arg1, m_APInt(Val)) &&
1837  match(Other->getArgOperand(0), m_Value(X)) &&
1838  match(Other->getArgOperand(1), m_APInt(Val2))) {
1839  if (IsUnsigned)
1840  NewVal = Val->uadd_sat(*Val2);
1841  else if (Val->isNonNegative() == Val2->isNonNegative()) {
1842  bool Overflow;
1843  NewVal = Val->sadd_ov(*Val2, Overflow);
1844  if (Overflow) {
1845  // Both adds together may add more than SignedMaxValue
1846  // without saturating the final result.
1847  break;
1848  }
1849  } else {
1850  // Cannot fold saturated addition with different signs.
1851  break;
1852  }
1853 
1854  return replaceInstUsesWith(
1855  *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
1856  IID, X, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), NewVal)));
1857  }
1858  }
1859  break;
1860  }
1861 
1862  case Intrinsic::minnum:
1863  case Intrinsic::maxnum:
1864  case Intrinsic::minimum:
1865  case Intrinsic::maximum: {
1866  Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
1867  Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1868  Value *X, *Y;
1869  if (match(Arg0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(Arg1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Y))) &&
1870  (Arg0->hasOneUse() || Arg1->hasOneUse())) {
1871  // If both operands are negated, invert the call and negate the result:
1872  // min(-X, -Y) --> -(max(X, Y))
1873  // max(-X, -Y) --> -(min(X, Y))
1874  Intrinsic::ID NewIID;
1875  switch (IID) {
1876  case Intrinsic::maxnum:
1877  NewIID = Intrinsic::minnum;
1878  break;
1879  case Intrinsic::minnum:
1880  NewIID = Intrinsic::maxnum;
1881  break;
1882  case Intrinsic::maximum:
1883  NewIID = Intrinsic::minimum;
1884  break;
1885  case Intrinsic::minimum:
1886  NewIID = Intrinsic::maximum;
1887  break;
1888  default:
1889  llvm_unreachable("unexpected intrinsic ID");
1890  }
1891  Value *NewCall = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(NewIID, X, Y, II);
1892  Instruction *FNeg = UnaryOperator::CreateFNeg(NewCall);
1893  FNeg->copyIRFlags(II);
1894  return FNeg;
1895  }
1896 
1897  // m(m(X, C2), C1) -> m(X, C)
1898  const APFloat *C1, *C2;
1899  if (auto *M = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Arg0)) {
1900  if (M->getIntrinsicID() == IID && match(Arg1, m_APFloat(C1)) &&
1901  ((match(M->getArgOperand(0), m_Value(X)) &&
1902  match(M->getArgOperand(1), m_APFloat(C2))) ||
1903  (match(M->getArgOperand(1), m_Value(X)) &&
1904  match(M->getArgOperand(0), m_APFloat(C2))))) {
1905  APFloat Res(0.0);
1906  switch (IID) {
1907  case Intrinsic::maxnum:
1908  Res = maxnum(*C1, *C2);
1909  break;
1910  case Intrinsic::minnum:
1911  Res = minnum(*C1, *C2);
1912  break;
1913  case Intrinsic::maximum:
1914  Res = maximum(*C1, *C2);
1915  break;
1916  case Intrinsic::minimum:
1917  Res = minimum(*C1, *C2);
1918  break;
1919  default:
1920  llvm_unreachable("unexpected intrinsic ID");
1921  }
1922  Instruction *NewCall = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
1923  IID, X, ConstantFP::get(Arg0->getType(), Res), II);
1924  // TODO: Conservatively intersecting FMF. If Res == C2, the transform
1925  // was a simplification (so Arg0 and its original flags could
1926  // propagate?)
1927  NewCall->andIRFlags(M);
1928  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
1929  }
1930  }
1931 
1932  // m((fpext X), (fpext Y)) -> fpext (m(X, Y))
1933  if (match(Arg0, m_OneUse(m_FPExt(m_Value(X)))) &&
1934  match(Arg1, m_OneUse(m_FPExt(m_Value(Y)))) &&
1935  X->getType() == Y->getType()) {
1936  Value *NewCall =
1937  Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(IID, X, Y, II, II->getName());
1938  return new FPExtInst(NewCall, II->getType());
1939  }
1940 
1941  // max X, -X --> fabs X
1942  // min X, -X --> -(fabs X)
1943  // TODO: Remove one-use limitation? That is obviously better for max.
1944  // It would be an extra instruction for min (fnabs), but that is
1945  // still likely better for analysis and codegen.
1946  if ((match(Arg0, m_OneUse(m_FNeg(m_Value(X)))) && Arg1 == X) ||
1947  (match(Arg1, m_OneUse(m_FNeg(m_Value(X)))) && Arg0 == X)) {
1948  Value *R = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, X, II);
1949  if (IID == Intrinsic::minimum || IID == Intrinsic::minnum)
1950  R = Builder.CreateFNegFMF(R, II);
1951  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, R);
1952  }
1953 
1954  break;
1955  }
1956  case Intrinsic::matrix_multiply: {
1957  // Optimize negation in matrix multiplication.
1958 
1959  // -A * -B -> A * B
1960  Value *A, *B;
1961  if (match(II->getArgOperand(0), m_FNeg(m_Value(A))) &&
1962  match(II->getArgOperand(1), m_FNeg(m_Value(B)))) {
1963  replaceOperand(*II, 0, A);
1964  replaceOperand(*II, 1, B);
1965  return II;
1966  }
1967 
1968  Value *Op0 = II->getOperand(0);
1969  Value *Op1 = II->getOperand(1);
1970  Value *OpNotNeg, *NegatedOp;
1971  unsigned NegatedOpArg, OtherOpArg;
1972  if (match(Op0, m_FNeg(m_Value(OpNotNeg)))) {
1973  NegatedOp = Op0;
1974  NegatedOpArg = 0;
1975  OtherOpArg = 1;
1976  } else if (match(Op1, m_FNeg(m_Value(OpNotNeg)))) {
1977  NegatedOp = Op1;
1978  NegatedOpArg = 1;
1979  OtherOpArg = 0;
1980  } else
1981  // Multiplication doesn't have a negated operand.
1982  break;
1983 
1984  // Only optimize if the negated operand has only one use.
1985  if (!NegatedOp->hasOneUse())
1986  break;
1987 
1988  Value *OtherOp = II->getOperand(OtherOpArg);
1989  VectorType *RetTy = cast<VectorType>(II->getType());
1990  VectorType *NegatedOpTy = cast<VectorType>(NegatedOp->getType());
1991  VectorType *OtherOpTy = cast<VectorType>(OtherOp->getType());
1992  ElementCount NegatedCount = NegatedOpTy->getElementCount();
1993  ElementCount OtherCount = OtherOpTy->getElementCount();
1994  ElementCount RetCount = RetTy->getElementCount();
1995  // (-A) * B -> A * (-B), if it is cheaper to negate B and vice versa.
1996  if (ElementCount::isKnownGT(NegatedCount, OtherCount) &&
1997  ElementCount::isKnownLT(OtherCount, RetCount)) {
1998  Value *InverseOtherOp = Builder.CreateFNeg(OtherOp);
1999  replaceOperand(*II, NegatedOpArg, OpNotNeg);
2000  replaceOperand(*II, OtherOpArg, InverseOtherOp);
2001  return II;
2002  }
2003  // (-A) * B -> -(A * B), if it is cheaper to negate the result
2004  if (ElementCount::isKnownGT(NegatedCount, RetCount)) {
2005  SmallVector<Value *, 5> NewArgs(II->args());
2006  NewArgs[NegatedOpArg] = OpNotNeg;
2007  Instruction *NewMul =
2008  Builder.CreateIntrinsic(II->getType(), IID, NewArgs, II);
2009  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Builder.CreateFNegFMF(NewMul, II));
2010  }
2011  break;
2012  }
2013  case Intrinsic::fmuladd: {
2014  // Canonicalize fast fmuladd to the separate fmul + fadd.
2015  if (II->isFast()) {
2016  BuilderTy::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(Builder);
2017  Builder.setFastMathFlags(II->getFastMathFlags());
2018  Value *Mul = Builder.CreateFMul(II->getArgOperand(0),
2019  II->getArgOperand(1));
2020  Value *Add = Builder.CreateFAdd(Mul, II->getArgOperand(2));
2021  Add->takeName(II);
2022  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Add);
2023  }
2024 
2025  // Try to simplify the underlying FMul.
2026  if (Value *V = simplifyFMulInst(II->getArgOperand(0), II->getArgOperand(1),
2027  II->getFastMathFlags(),
2028  SQ.getWithInstruction(II))) {
2029  auto *FAdd = BinaryOperator::CreateFAdd(V, II->getArgOperand(2));
2030  FAdd->copyFastMathFlags(II);
2031  return FAdd;
2032  }
2033 
2034  [[fallthrough]];
2035  }
2036  case Intrinsic::fma: {
2037  // fma fneg(x), fneg(y), z -> fma x, y, z
2038  Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2039  Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2040  Value *X, *Y;
2041  if (match(Src0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(Src1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Y)))) {
2042  replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
2043  replaceOperand(*II, 1, Y);
2044  return II;
2045  }
2046 
2047  // fma fabs(x), fabs(x), z -> fma x, x, z
2048  if (match(Src0, m_FAbs(m_Value(X))) &&
2049  match(Src1, m_FAbs(m_Specific(X)))) {
2050  replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
2051  replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);
2052  return II;
2053  }
2054 
2055  // Try to simplify the underlying FMul. We can only apply simplifications
2056  // that do not require rounding.
2057  if (Value *V = simplifyFMAFMul(II->getArgOperand(0), II->getArgOperand(1),
2058  II->getFastMathFlags(),
2059  SQ.getWithInstruction(II))) {
2060  auto *FAdd = BinaryOperator::CreateFAdd(V, II->getArgOperand(2));
2061  FAdd->copyFastMathFlags(II);
2062  return FAdd;
2063  }
2064 
2065  // fma x, y, 0 -> fmul x, y
2066  // This is always valid for -0.0, but requires nsz for +0.0 as
2067  // -0.0 + 0.0 = 0.0, which would not be the same as the fmul on its own.
2068  if (match(II->getArgOperand(2), m_NegZeroFP()) ||
2069  (match(II->getArgOperand(2), m_PosZeroFP()) &&
2070  II->getFastMathFlags().noSignedZeros()))
2071  return BinaryOperator::CreateFMulFMF(Src0, Src1, II);
2072 
2073  break;
2074  }
2075  case Intrinsic::copysign: {
2076  Value *Mag = II->getArgOperand(0), *Sign = II->getArgOperand(1);
2077  if (SignBitMustBeZero(Sign, &TLI)) {
2078  // If we know that the sign argument is positive, reduce to FABS:
2079  // copysign Mag, +Sign --> fabs Mag
2080  Value *Fabs = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, Mag, II);
2081  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Fabs);
2082  }
2083  // TODO: There should be a ValueTracking sibling like SignBitMustBeOne.
2084  const APFloat *C;
2085  if (match(Sign, m_APFloat(C)) && C->isNegative()) {
2086  // If we know that the sign argument is negative, reduce to FNABS:
2087  // copysign Mag, -Sign --> fneg (fabs Mag)
2088  Value *Fabs = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::fabs, Mag, II);
2089  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Builder.CreateFNegFMF(Fabs, II));
2090  }
2091 
2092  // Propagate sign argument through nested calls:
2093  // copysign Mag, (copysign ?, X) --> copysign Mag, X
2094  Value *X;
2095  if (match(Sign, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(), m_Value(X))))
2096  return replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);
2097 
2098  // Peek through changes of magnitude's sign-bit. This call rewrites those:
2099  // copysign (fabs X), Sign --> copysign X, Sign
2100  // copysign (fneg X), Sign --> copysign X, Sign
2101  if (match(Mag, m_FAbs(m_Value(X))) || match(Mag, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))))
2102  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, X);
2103 
2104  break;
2105  }
2106  case Intrinsic::fabs: {
2107  Value *Cond, *TVal, *FVal;
2108  if (match(II->getArgOperand(0),
2109  m_Select(m_Value(Cond), m_Value(TVal), m_Value(FVal)))) {
2110  // fabs (select Cond, TrueC, FalseC) --> select Cond, AbsT, AbsF
2111  if (isa<Constant>(TVal) && isa<Constant>(FVal)) {
2112  CallInst *AbsT = Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(), {TVal});
2113  CallInst *AbsF = Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(), {FVal});
2114  return SelectInst::Create(Cond, AbsT, AbsF);
2115  }
2116  // fabs (select Cond, -FVal, FVal) --> fabs FVal
2117  if (match(TVal, m_FNeg(m_Specific(FVal))))
2118  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, FVal);
2119  // fabs (select Cond, TVal, -TVal) --> fabs TVal
2120  if (match(FVal, m_FNeg(m_Specific(TVal))))
2121  return replaceOperand(*II, 0, TVal);
2122  }
2123 
2124  Value *Magnitude, *Sign;
2125  if (match(II->getArgOperand(0),
2126  m_CopySign(m_Value(Magnitude), m_Value(Sign)))) {
2127  // fabs (copysign x, y) -> (fabs x)
2128  CallInst *AbsSign =
2129  Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(), {Magnitude});
2130  AbsSign->copyFastMathFlags(II);
2131  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, AbsSign);
2132  }
2133 
2134  [[fallthrough]];
2135  }
2136  case Intrinsic::ceil:
2137  case Intrinsic::floor:
2138  case Intrinsic::round:
2139  case Intrinsic::roundeven:
2140  case Intrinsic::nearbyint:
2141  case Intrinsic::rint:
2142  case Intrinsic::trunc: {

2146  Value *NarrowII = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(IID, ExtSrc, II);
2147  return new FPExtInst(NarrowII, II->getType());

2150  }
2151  case Intrinsic::cos:

2172  }
2173  case Intrinsic::ptrauth_auth:
2174  case Intrinsic::ptrauth_resign: {
2175  // (sign|resign) + (auth|resign) can be folded by omitting the middle
2176  // sign+auth component if the key and discriminator match.
2177  bool NeedSign = II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::ptrauth_resign;
2178  Value *Key = II->getArgOperand(1);
2179  Value *Disc = II->getArgOperand(2);
2180 
2181  // AuthKey will be the key we need to end up authenticating against in
2182  // whatever we replace this sequence with.
2183  Value *AuthKey = nullptr, *AuthDisc = nullptr, *BasePtr;
2184  if (auto CI = dyn_cast<CallBase>(II->getArgOperand(0))) {
2185  BasePtr = CI->getArgOperand(0);
2186  if (CI->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::ptrauth_sign) {
2187  if (CI->getArgOperand(1) != Key || CI->getArgOperand(2) != Disc)
2188  break;
2189  } else if (CI->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::ptrauth_resign) {
2190  if (CI->getArgOperand(3) != Key || CI->getArgOperand(4) != Disc)
2191  break;
2192  AuthKey = CI->getArgOperand(1);
2193  AuthDisc = CI->getArgOperand(2);
2194  } else
2195  break;
2196  } else
2197  break;

2200  if (AuthKey && NeedSign) {
2201  // resign(0,1) + resign(1,2) = resign(0, 2)
2202  NewIntrin = Intrinsic::ptrauth_resign;
2203  } else if (AuthKey) {
2204  // resign(0,1) + auth(1) = auth(0)
2205  NewIntrin = Intrinsic::ptrauth_auth;
2206  } else if (NeedSign) {
2207  // sign(0) + resign(0, 1) = sign(1)
2208  NewIntrin = Intrinsic::ptrauth_sign;
2209  } else {
2210  // sign(0) + auth(0) = nop
2211  replaceInstUsesWith(*II, BasePtr);
2212  eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
2213  return nullptr;
2214  }
2215

2217  CallArgs.push_back(BasePtr);
2218  if (AuthKey) {
2219  CallArgs.push_back(AuthKey);
2220  CallArgs.push_back(AuthDisc);
2221  }
2222 
2223  if (NeedSign) {
2224  CallArgs.push_back(II->getArgOperand(3));
2225  CallArgs.push_back(II->getArgOperand(4));
2226  }
2227

2229  return CallInst::Create(NewFn, CallArgs);
2230  }
2231  case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vtbl1:

2237  case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmulls:
2238  case Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmullu:
2239  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_smull:
2240  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_umull: {
2241  Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2242  Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2243 
2244  // Handle mul by zero first:
2245  if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(Arg0) || isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(Arg1)) {
2246  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, ConstantAggregateZero::get(II->getType()));
2247  }

2250  bool Zext = (IID == Intrinsic::arm_neon_vmullu ||
2251  IID == Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_umull);

2256  CV1 = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(CV1, NewVT, /*isSigned=*/!Zext);
2257

2260

2262  std::swap(Arg0, Arg1);
2263  }

2266  if (Constant *CV1 = dyn_cast<Constant>(Arg1))
2267  if (ConstantInt *Splat =
2268  dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(CV1->getSplatValue()))

2271  /*isSigned=*/!Zext);

2274  }

2292  case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandvrt:

2298  ID0 != Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vandqrt_128B)
2299  break;
2300  Value *Bytes = Op0->getArgOperand(1), *Mask = II->getArgOperand(1);
2301  uint64_t Bytes1 = computeKnownBits(Bytes, 0, Op0).One.getZExtValue();
2302  uint64_t Mask1 = computeKnownBits(Mask, 0, II).One.getZExtValue();
2303  // Check if every byte has common bits in Bytes and Mask.
2304  uint64_t C = Bytes1 & Mask1;
2305  if ((C & 0xFF) && (C & 0xFF00) && (C & 0xFF0000) && (C & 0xFF000000))
2306  return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Op0->getArgOperand(0));
2307  }

2309  }
2310  case Intrinsic::stackrestore: {
2311  enum class ClassifyResult {
2312  None,
2313  Alloca,
2314  StackRestore,
2315  CallWithSideEffects,
2316  };
2317  auto Classify = [](const Instruction *I) {
2318  if (isa<AllocaInst>(I))
2319  return ClassifyResult::Alloca;
2320 
2321  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(I)) {
2322  if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(CI)) {
2323  if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::stackrestore)
2324  return ClassifyResult::StackRestore;
2325 
2326  if (II->mayHaveSideEffects())
2327  return ClassifyResult::CallWithSideEffects;
2328  } else {
2329  // Consider all non-intrinsic calls to be side effects
2330  return ClassifyResult::CallWithSideEffects;
2331  }
2332  }
2333 
2334  return ClassifyResult::None;
2335  };
2336 
2337  // If the stacksave and the stackrestore are in the same BB, and there is
2338  // no intervening call, alloca, or stackrestore of a different stacksave,
2339  // remove the restore. This can happen when variable allocas are DCE'd.
2340  if (IntrinsicInst *SS = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(II->getArgOperand(0))) {
2341  if (SS->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::stacksave &&
2342  SS->getParent() == II->getParent()) {
2343  BasicBlock::iterator BI(SS);
2344  bool CannotRemove = false;
2345  for (++BI; &*BI != II; ++BI) {
2346  switch (Classify(&*BI)) {
2347  case ClassifyResult::None:
2348  // So far so good, look at next instructions.
2349  break;
2350 
2351  case ClassifyResult::StackRestore:
2352  // If we found an intervening stackrestore for a different
2353  // stacksave, we can't remove the stackrestore. Otherwise, continue.
2354  if (cast<IntrinsicInst>(*BI).getArgOperand(0) != SS)
2355  CannotRemove = true;
2356  break;
2357 
2358  case ClassifyResult::Alloca:
2359  case ClassifyResult::CallWithSideEffects:
2360  // If we found an alloca, a non-intrinsic call, or an intrinsic
2361  // call with side effects, we can't remove the stackrestore.
2362  CannotRemove = true;
2363  break;
2364  }
2365  if (CannotRemove)
2366  break;
2367  }
2368 
2369  if (!CannotRemove)
2370  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
2371  }
2372  }
2373 
2374  // Scan down this block to see if there is another stack restore in the
2375  // same block without an intervening call/alloca.
2376  BasicBlock::iterator BI(II);
2377  Instruction *TI = II->getParent()->getTerminator();
2378  bool CannotRemove = false;
2379  for (++BI; &*BI != TI; ++BI) {
2380  switch (Classify(&*BI)) {
2381  case ClassifyResult::None:
2382  // So far so good, look at next instructions.
2383  break;
2384 
2385  case ClassifyResult::StackRestore:
2386  // If there is a stackrestore below this one, remove this one.
2387  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
2388 
2389  case ClassifyResult::Alloca:
2390  case ClassifyResult::CallWithSideEffects:
2391  // If we found an alloca, a non-intrinsic call, or an intrinsic call
2392  // with side effects (such as llvm.stacksave and llvm.read_register),
2393  // we can't remove the stack restore.
2394  CannotRemove = true;
2395  break;
2396  }
2397  if (CannotRemove)
2398  break;
2399  }
2400 
2401  // If the stack restore is in a return, resume, or unwind block and if there
2402  // are no allocas or calls between the restore and the return, nuke the
2403  // restore.
2404  if (!CannotRemove && (isa<ReturnInst>(TI) || isa<ResumeInst>(TI)))
2405  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
2406  break;
2407  }
2408  case Intrinsic::lifetime_end:
2409  // Asan needs to poison memory to detect invalid access which is possible
2410  // even for empty lifetime range.
2411  if (II->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeAddress) ||
2412  II->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeMemory) ||
2413  II->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeHWAddress))
2414  break;
2415 
2416  if (removeTriviallyEmptyRange(*II, *this, [](const IntrinsicInst &I) {
2417  return I.getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::lifetime_start;
2418  }))
2419  return nullptr;
2420  break;
2421  case Intrinsic::assume: {
2422  Value *IIOperand = II->getArgOperand(0);
2423  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 4> OpBundles;
2424  II->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
2425 
2426  /// This will remove the boolean Condition from the assume given as
2427  /// argument and remove the assume if it becomes useless.
2428  /// always returns nullptr for use as a return values.
2429  auto RemoveConditionFromAssume = [&](Instruction *Assume) -> Instruction * {
2430  assert(isa<AssumeInst>(Assume));
2431  if (isAssumeWithEmptyBundle(*cast<AssumeInst>(II)))
2432  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
2433  replaceUse(II->getOperandUse(0), ConstantInt::getTrue(II->getContext()));
2434  return nullptr;
2435  };
2436  // Remove an assume if it is followed by an identical assume.
2437  // TODO: Do we need this? Unless there are conflicting assumptions, the
2438  // computeKnownBits(IIOperand) below here eliminates redundant assumes.
2439  Instruction *Next = II->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
2440  if (match(Next, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::assume>(m_Specific(IIOperand))))
2441  return RemoveConditionFromAssume(Next);
2442 
2443  // Canonicalize assume(a && b) -> assume(a); assume(b);
2444  // Note: New assumption intrinsics created here are registered by
2445  // the InstCombineIRInserter object.
2446  FunctionType *AssumeIntrinsicTy = II->getFunctionType();
2447  Value *AssumeIntrinsic = II->getCalledOperand();
2448  Value *A, *B;
2449  if (match(IIOperand, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) {
2450  Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic, A, OpBundles,
2451  II->getName());
2452  Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic, B, II->getName());
2453  return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
2454  }
2455  // assume(!(a || b)) -> assume(!a); assume(!b);
2456  if (match(IIOperand, m_Not(m_LogicalOr(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))))) {
2457  Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic,
2458  Builder.CreateNot(A), OpBundles, II->getName());
2459  Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic,
2460  Builder.CreateNot(B), II->getName());
2461  return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
2462  }
2463 
2464  // assume( (load addr) != null ) -> add 'nonnull' metadata to load
2465  // (if assume is valid at the load)
2466  CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
2467  Instruction *LHS;
2468  if (match(IIOperand, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Instruction(LHS), m_Zero())) &&
2469  Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Load &&
2470  LHS->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
2471  isValidAssumeForContext(II, LHS, &DT)) {
2472  MDNode *MD = MDNode::get(II->getContext(), std::nullopt);
2473  LHS->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull, MD);
2474  return RemoveConditionFromAssume(II);
2475 
2476  // TODO: apply nonnull return attributes to calls and invokes
2477  // TODO: apply range metadata for range check patterns?
2478  }
2479 
2480  // Convert nonnull assume like:
2481  // %A = icmp ne i32* %PTR, null
2482  // call void @llvm.assume(i1 %A)
2483  // into
2484  // call void @llvm.assume(i1 true) [ "nonnull"(i32* %PTR) ]
2485  if (EnableKnowledgeRetention &&
2486  match(IIOperand, m_Cmp(Pred, m_Value(A), m_Zero())) &&
2487  Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE && A->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
2488  if (auto *Replacement = buildAssumeFromKnowledge(
2489  {RetainedKnowledge{Attribute::NonNull, 0, A}}, Next, &AC, &DT)) {
2490 
2491  Replacement->insertBefore(Next);
2492  AC.registerAssumption(Replacement);
2493  return RemoveConditionFromAssume(II);
2494  }
2495  }
2496 
2497  // Convert alignment assume like:
2498  // %B = ptrtoint i32* %A to i64
2499  // %C = and i64 %B, Constant
2500  // %D = icmp eq i64 %C, 0
2501  // call void @llvm.assume(i1 %D)
2502  // into
2503  // call void @llvm.assume(i1 true) [ "align"(i32* [[A]], i64 Constant + 1)]
2504  uint64_t AlignMask;
2505  if (EnableKnowledgeRetention &&
2506  match(IIOperand,
2507  m_Cmp(Pred, m_And(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(AlignMask)),
2508  m_Zero())) &&
2509  Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ) {
2510  if (isPowerOf2_64(AlignMask + 1)) {
2511  uint64_t Offset = 0;
2512  match(A, m_Add(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(Offset)));
2513  if (match(A, m_PtrToInt(m_Value(A)))) {
2514  /// Note: this doesn't preserve the offset information but merges
2515  /// offset and alignment.
2516  /// TODO: we can generate a GEP instead of merging the alignment with
2517  /// the offset.
2518  RetainedKnowledge RK{Attribute::Alignment,
2519  (unsigned)MinAlign(Offset, AlignMask + 1), A};
2520  if (auto *Replacement =
2521  buildAssumeFromKnowledge(RK, Next, &AC, &DT)) {
2522 
2523  Replacement->insertAfter(II);
2524  AC.registerAssumption(Replacement);
2525  }
2526  return RemoveConditionFromAssume(II);
2527  }
2528  }
2529  }
2530 
2531  /// Canonicalize Knowledge in operand bundles.
2532  if (EnableKnowledgeRetention && II->hasOperandBundles()) {
2533  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < II->getNumOperandBundles(); Idx++) {
2534  auto &BOI = II->bundle_op_info_begin()[Idx];
2535  RetainedKnowledge RK =
2536  llvm::getKnowledgeFromBundle(cast<AssumeInst>(*II), BOI);
2537  if (BOI.End - BOI.Begin > 2)
2538  continue; // Prevent reducing knowledge in an align with offset since
2539  // extracting a RetainedKnowledge from them looses offset
2540  // information
2541  RetainedKnowledge CanonRK =
2542  llvm::simplifyRetainedKnowledge(cast<AssumeInst>(II), RK,
2543  &getAssumptionCache(),
2544  &getDominatorTree());
2545  if (CanonRK == RK)
2546  continue;
2547  if (!CanonRK) {
2548  if (BOI.End - BOI.Begin > 0) {
2549  Worklist.pushValue(II->op_begin()[BOI.Begin]);
2550  Value::dropDroppableUse(II->op_begin()[BOI.Begin]);
2551  }
2552  continue;
2553  }
2554  assert(RK.AttrKind == CanonRK.AttrKind);
2555  if (BOI.End - BOI.Begin > 0)
2556  II->op_begin()[BOI.Begin].set(CanonRK.WasOn);
2557  if (BOI.End - BOI.Begin > 1)
2558  II->op_begin()[BOI.Begin + 1].set(ConstantInt::get(
2559  Type::getInt64Ty(II->getContext()), CanonRK.ArgValue));
2560  if (RK.WasOn)
2561  Worklist.pushValue(RK.WasOn);
2562  return II;
2563  }
2564  }
2565 
2566  // If there is a dominating assume with the same condition as this one,
2567  // then this one is redundant, and should be removed.
2568  KnownBits Known(1);
2569  computeKnownBits(IIOperand, Known, 0, II);
2570  if (Known.isAllOnes() && isAssumeWithEmptyBundle(cast<AssumeInst>(*II)))
2571  return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
2572 
2573  // Update the cache of affected values for this assumption (we might be
2574  // here because we just simplified the condition).
2575  AC.updateAffectedValues(cast<AssumeInst>(II));
2576  break;
2577  }
2578  case Intrinsic::experimental_guard: {
2579  // Is this guard followed by another guard? We scan forward over a small
2580  // fixed window of instructions to handle common cases with conditions
2581  // computed between guards.
2582  Instruction *NextInst = II->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
2583  for (unsigned i = 0; i < GuardWideningWindow; i++) {
2584  // Note: Using context-free form to avoid compile time blow up
2585  if (!isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(NextInst))
2586  break;
2587  NextInst = NextInst->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
2588  }
2589  Value *NextCond = nullptr;
2590  if (match(NextInst,
2591  m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::experimental_guard>(m_Value(NextCond)))) {
2592  Value *CurrCond = II->getArgOperand(0);
2593 
2594  // Remove a guard that it is immediately preceded by an identical guard.
2595  // Otherwise canonicalize guard(a); guard(b) -> guard(a & b).
2596  if (CurrCond != NextCond) {
2597  Instruction *MoveI = II->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
2598  while (MoveI != NextInst) {
2599  auto *Temp = MoveI;
2600  MoveI = MoveI->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
2601  Temp->moveBefore(II);
2602  }
2603  replaceOperand(*II, 0, Builder.CreateAnd(CurrCond, NextCond));
2604  }
2605  eraseInstFromFunction(*NextInst);
2606  return II;
2607  }
2608  break;
2609  }
2610  case Intrinsic::vector_insert: {
2611  Value *Vec = II->getArgOperand(0);
2612  Value *SubVec = II->getArgOperand(1);
2613  Value *Idx = II->getArgOperand(2);
2614  auto *DstTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(II->getType());
2615  auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType());
2616  auto *SubVecTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(SubVec->getType());
2617 
2618  // Only canonicalize if the destination vector, Vec, and SubVec are all
2619  // fixed vectors.
2620  if (DstTy && VecTy && SubVecTy) {
2621  unsigned DstNumElts = DstTy->getNumElements();
2622  unsigned VecNumElts = VecTy->getNumElements();
2623  unsigned SubVecNumElts = SubVecTy->getNumElements();
2624  unsigned IdxN = cast<ConstantInt>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
2625 
2626  // An insert that entirely overwrites Vec with SubVec is a nop.
2627  if (VecNumElts == SubVecNumElts)
2628  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, SubVec);
2629 
2630  // Widen SubVec into a vector of the same width as Vec, since
2631  // shufflevector requires the two input vectors to be the same width.
2632  // Elements beyond the bounds of SubVec within the widened vector are
2633  // undefined.
2634  SmallVector<int, 8> WidenMask;
2635  unsigned i;
2636  for (i = 0; i != SubVecNumElts; ++i)
2637  WidenMask.push_back(i);
2638  for (; i != VecNumElts; ++i)
2639  WidenMask.push_back(UndefMaskElem);
2640 
2641  Value *WidenShuffle = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(SubVec, WidenMask);
2642 
2643  SmallVector<int, 8> Mask;
2644  for (unsigned i = 0; i != IdxN; ++i)
2645  Mask.push_back(i);
2646  for (unsigned i = DstNumElts; i != DstNumElts + SubVecNumElts; ++i)
2647  Mask.push_back(i);
2648  for (unsigned i = IdxN + SubVecNumElts; i != DstNumElts; ++i)
2649  Mask.push_back(i);
2650 
2651  Value *Shuffle = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, WidenShuffle, Mask);
2652  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Shuffle);
2653  }
2654  break;
2655  }
2656  case Intrinsic::vector_extract: {
2657  Value *Vec = II->getArgOperand(0);
2658  Value *Idx = II->getArgOperand(1);
2659 
2660  Type *ReturnType = II->getType();
2661  // (extract_vector (insert_vector InsertTuple, InsertValue, InsertIdx),
2662  // ExtractIdx)
2663  unsigned ExtractIdx = cast<ConstantInt>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
2664  Value *InsertTuple, *InsertIdx, *InsertValue;
2665  if (match(Vec, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::vector_insert>(m_Value(InsertTuple),
2666  m_Value(InsertValue),
2667  m_Value(InsertIdx))) &&
2668  InsertValue->getType() == ReturnType) {
2669  unsigned Index = cast<ConstantInt>(InsertIdx)->getZExtValue();
2670  // Case where we get the same index right after setting it.
2671  // extract.vector(insert.vector(InsertTuple, InsertValue, Idx), Idx) -->
2672  // InsertValue
2673  if (ExtractIdx == Index)
2674  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, InsertValue);
2675  // If we are getting a different index than what was set in the
2676  // insert.vector intrinsic. We can just set the input tuple to the one up
2677  // in the chain. extract.vector(insert.vector(InsertTuple, InsertValue,
2678  // InsertIndex), ExtractIndex)
2679  // --> extract.vector(InsertTuple, ExtractIndex)
2680  else
2681  return replaceOperand(CI, 0, InsertTuple);
2682  }
2683 
2684  auto *DstTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(ReturnType);
2685  auto *VecTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType());
2686 
2687  // Only canonicalize if the the destination vector and Vec are fixed
2688  // vectors.
2689  if (DstTy && VecTy) {
2690  unsigned DstNumElts = DstTy->getNumElements();
2691  unsigned VecNumElts = VecTy->getNumElements();
2692  unsigned IdxN = cast<ConstantInt>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
2693 
2694  // Extracting the entirety of Vec is a nop.
2695  if (VecNumElts == DstNumElts) {
2696  replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Vec);
2697  return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
2698  }
2699 
2700  SmallVector<int, 8> Mask;
2701  for (unsigned i = 0; i != DstNumElts; ++i)
2702  Mask.push_back(IdxN + i);
2703 
2704  Value *Shuffle = Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, Mask);
2705  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Shuffle);
2706  }
2707  break;
2708  }
2709  case Intrinsic::experimental_vector_reverse: {
2710  Value *BO0, *BO1, *X, *Y;
2711  Value *Vec = II->getArgOperand(0);
2712  if (match(Vec, m_OneUse(m_BinOp(m_Value(BO0), m_Value(BO1))))) {
2713  auto *OldBinOp = cast<BinaryOperator>(Vec);
2714  if (match(BO0, m_VecReverse(m_Value(X)))) {
2715  // rev(binop rev(X), rev(Y)) --> binop X, Y
2716  if (match(BO1, m_VecReverse(m_Value(Y))))
2717  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI,
2718  BinaryOperator::CreateWithCopiedFlags(
2719  OldBinOp->getOpcode(), X, Y, OldBinOp,
2720  OldBinOp->getName(), II));
2721  // rev(binop rev(X), BO1Splat) --> binop X, BO1Splat
2722  if (isSplatValue(BO1))
2723  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI,
2724  BinaryOperator::CreateWithCopiedFlags(
2725  OldBinOp->getOpcode(), X, BO1,
2726  OldBinOp, OldBinOp->getName(), II));
2727  }
2728  // rev(binop BO0Splat, rev(Y)) --> binop BO0Splat, Y
2729  if (match(BO1, m_VecReverse(m_Value(Y))) && isSplatValue(BO0))
2730  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, BinaryOperator::CreateWithCopiedFlags(
2731  OldBinOp->getOpcode(), BO0, Y,
2732  OldBinOp, OldBinOp->getName(), II));
2733  }
2734  // rev(unop rev(X)) --> unop X
2735  if (match(Vec, m_OneUse(m_UnOp(m_VecReverse(m_Value(X)))))) {
2736  auto *OldUnOp = cast<UnaryOperator>(Vec);
2737  auto *NewUnOp = UnaryOperator::CreateWithCopiedFlags(
2738  OldUnOp->getOpcode(), X, OldUnOp, OldUnOp->getName(), II);
2739  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, NewUnOp);
2740  }
2741  break;
2742  }
2743  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or:
2744  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and: {
2745  // Canonicalize logical or/and reductions:
2746  // Or reduction for i1 is represented as:
2747  // %val = bitcast <ReduxWidth x i1> to iReduxWidth
2748  // %res = cmp ne iReduxWidth %val, 0
2749  // And reduction for i1 is represented as:
2750  // %val = bitcast <ReduxWidth x i1> to iReduxWidth
2751  // %res = cmp eq iReduxWidth %val, 11111
2752  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2753  Value *Vect;
2754  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2755  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2756  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2757  Value *Res = Builder.CreateBitCast(
2758  Vect, Builder.getIntNTy(FTy->getNumElements()));
2759  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and) {
2760  Res = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
2761  Res, ConstantInt::getAllOnesValue(Res->getType()));
2762  } else {
2763  assert(IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or &&
2764  "Expected or reduction.");
2765  Res = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Res);
2766  }
2767  if (Arg != Vect)
2768  Res = Builder.CreateCast(cast<CastInst>(Arg)->getOpcode(), Res,
2769  II->getType());
2770  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2771  }
2772  }
2773  [[fallthrough]];
2774  }
2775  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add: {
2776  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add) {
2777  // Convert vector_reduce_add(ZExt(<n x i1>)) to
2778  // ZExtOrTrunc(ctpop(bitcast <n x i1> to in)).
2779  // Convert vector_reduce_add(SExt(<n x i1>)) to
2780  // -ZExtOrTrunc(ctpop(bitcast <n x i1> to in)).
2781  // Convert vector_reduce_add(<n x i1>) to
2782  // Trunc(ctpop(bitcast <n x i1> to in)).
2783  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2784  Value *Vect;
2785  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2786  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2787  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2788  Value *V = Builder.CreateBitCast(
2789  Vect, Builder.getIntNTy(FTy->getNumElements()));
2790  Value *Res = Builder.CreateUnaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ctpop, V);
2791  if (Res->getType() != II->getType())
2792  Res = Builder.CreateZExtOrTrunc(Res, II->getType());
2793  if (Arg != Vect &&
2794  cast<Instruction>(Arg)->getOpcode() == Instruction::SExt)
2795  Res = Builder.CreateNeg(Res);
2796  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2797  }
2798  }
2799  }
2800  [[fallthrough]];
2801  }
2802  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor: {
2803  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor) {
2804  // Exclusive disjunction reduction over the vector with
2805  // (potentially-extended) i1 element type is actually a
2806  // (potentially-extended) arithmetic `add` reduction over the original
2807  // non-extended value:
2808  // vector_reduce_xor(?ext(<n x i1>))
2809  // -->
2810  // ?ext(vector_reduce_add(<n x i1>))
2811  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2812  Value *Vect;
2813  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2814  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2815  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2816  Value *Res = Builder.CreateAddReduce(Vect);
2817  if (Arg != Vect)
2818  Res = Builder.CreateCast(cast<CastInst>(Arg)->getOpcode(), Res,
2819  II->getType());
2820  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2821  }
2822  }
2823  }
2824  [[fallthrough]];
2825  }
2826  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul: {
2827  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul) {
2828  // Multiplicative reduction over the vector with (potentially-extended)
2829  // i1 element type is actually a (potentially zero-extended)
2830  // logical `and` reduction over the original non-extended value:
2831  // vector_reduce_mul(?ext(<n x i1>))
2832  // -->
2833  // zext(vector_reduce_and(<n x i1>))
2834  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2835  Value *Vect;
2836  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2837  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2838  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2839  Value *Res = Builder.CreateAndReduce(Vect);
2840  if (Res->getType() != II->getType())
2841  Res = Builder.CreateZExt(Res, II->getType());
2842  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2843  }
2844  }
2845  }
2846  [[fallthrough]];
2847  }
2848  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin:
2849  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax: {
2850  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin ||
2851  IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax) {
2852  // UMin/UMax reduction over the vector with (potentially-extended)
2853  // i1 element type is actually a (potentially-extended)
2854  // logical `and`/`or` reduction over the original non-extended value:
2855  // vector_reduce_u{min,max}(?ext(<n x i1>))
2856  // -->
2857  // ?ext(vector_reduce_{and,or}(<n x i1>))
2858  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2859  Value *Vect;
2860  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2861  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2862  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2863  Value *Res = IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin
2864  ? Builder.CreateAndReduce(Vect)
2865  : Builder.CreateOrReduce(Vect);
2866  if (Arg != Vect)
2867  Res = Builder.CreateCast(cast<CastInst>(Arg)->getOpcode(), Res,
2868  II->getType());
2869  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2870  }
2871  }
2872  }
2873  [[fallthrough]];
2874  }
2875  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin:
2876  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax: {
2877  if (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin ||
2878  IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax) {
2879  // SMin/SMax reduction over the vector with (potentially-extended)
2880  // i1 element type is actually a (potentially-extended)
2881  // logical `and`/`or` reduction over the original non-extended value:
2882  // vector_reduce_s{min,max}(<n x i1>)
2883  // -->
2884  // vector_reduce_{or,and}(<n x i1>)
2885  // and
2886  // vector_reduce_s{min,max}(sext(<n x i1>))
2887  // -->
2888  // sext(vector_reduce_{or,and}(<n x i1>))
2889  // and
2890  // vector_reduce_s{min,max}(zext(<n x i1>))
2891  // -->
2892  // zext(vector_reduce_{and,or}(<n x i1>))
2893  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(0);
2894  Value *Vect;
2895  if (match(Arg, m_ZExtOrSExtOrSelf(m_Value(Vect)))) {
2896  if (auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Vect->getType()))
2897  if (FTy->getElementType() == Builder.getInt1Ty()) {
2898  Instruction::CastOps ExtOpc = Instruction::CastOps::CastOpsEnd;
2899  if (Arg != Vect)
2900  ExtOpc = cast<CastInst>(Arg)->getOpcode();
2901  Value *Res = ((IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin) ==
2902  (ExtOpc == Instruction::CastOps::ZExt))
2903  ? Builder.CreateAndReduce(Vect)
2904  : Builder.CreateOrReduce(Vect);
2905  if (Arg != Vect)
2906  Res = Builder.CreateCast(ExtOpc, Res, II->getType());
2907  return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Res);
2908  }
2909  }
2910  }
2911  [[fallthrough]];
2912  }
2913  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmax:
2914  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmin:
2915  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd:
2916  case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmul: {
2917  bool CanBeReassociated = (IID != Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd &&
2918  IID != Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmul) ||
2919  II->hasAllowReassoc();
2920  const unsigned ArgIdx = (IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fadd ||
2921  IID == Intrinsic::vector_reduce_fmul)
2922  ? 1
2923  : 0;
2924  Value *Arg = II->getArgOperand(ArgIdx);
2925  Value *V;
2926  ArrayRef<int> Mask;
2927  if (!isa<FixedVectorType>(Arg->getType()) || !CanBeReassociated ||
2928  !match(Arg, m_Shuffle(m_Value(V), m_Undef(), m_Mask(Mask))) ||
2929  !cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(Arg)->isSingleSource())
2930  break;
2931  int Sz = Mask.size();
2932  SmallBitVector UsedIndices(Sz);
2933  for (int Idx : Mask) {
2934  if (Idx == UndefMaskElem || UsedIndices.test(Idx))
2935  break;
2936  UsedIndices.set(Idx);
2937  }
2938  // Can remove shuffle iff just shuffled elements, no repeats, undefs, or
2939  // other changes.
2940  if (UsedIndices.all()) {
2941  replaceUse(II->getOperandUse(ArgIdx), V);
2942  return nullptr;
2943  }
2944  break;
2945  }
2946  case Intrinsic::is_fpclass: {
2947  if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicIsFPClass(*II))
2948  return I;
2949  break;
2950  }
2951  default: {
2952  // Handle target specific intrinsics
2953  std::optional<Instruction *> V = targetInstCombineIntrinsic(*II);
2954  if (V)
2955  return *V;
2956  break;
2957  }
2958  }
2959 
2960  if (Instruction *Shuf = foldShuffledIntrinsicOperands(II, Builder))
2961  return Shuf;
2962 
2963  // Some intrinsics (like experimental_gc_statepoint) can be used in invoke
2964  // context, so it is handled in visitCallBase and we should trigger it.
2965  return visitCallBase(*II);
2966 }

2968 // Fence instruction simplification
2969 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::visitFenceInst(FenceInst &FI) {
2970  auto *NFI = dyn_cast<FenceInst>(FI.getNextNonDebugInstruction());
2971  // This check is solely here to handle arbitrary target-dependent syncscopes.
2972  // TODO: Can remove if does not matter in practice.
2973  if (NFI && FI.isIdenticalTo(NFI))
2974  return eraseInstFromFunction(FI);
2975 
2976  // Returns true if FI1 is identical or stronger fence than FI2.
2977  auto isIdenticalOrStrongerFence = [](FenceInst *FI1, FenceInst *FI2) {
2978  auto FI1SyncScope = FI1->getSyncScopeID();
2979  // Consider same scope, where scope is global or single-thread.
2980  if (FI1SyncScope != FI2->getSyncScopeID() ||
2981  (FI1SyncScope != SyncScope::System &&
2982  FI1SyncScope != SyncScope::SingleThread))
2983  return false;
2984 
2985  return isAtLeastOrStrongerThan(FI1->getOrdering(), FI2->getOrdering());
2986  };
2987  if (NFI && isIdenticalOrStrongerFence(NFI, &FI))
2988  return eraseInstFromFunction(FI);
2989 
2990  if (auto *PFI = dyn_cast_or_null<FenceInst>(FI.getPrevNonDebugInstruction()))
2991  if (isIdenticalOrStrongerFence(PFI, &FI))
2992  return eraseInstFromFunction(FI);
2993  return nullptr;
2994 }

3006 /// If this cast does not affect the value passed through the varargs area, we
3007 /// can eliminate the use of the cast.
3008 static bool isSafeToEliminateVarargsCast(const CallBase &Call,
3009  const DataLayout &DL,
3010  const CastInst *const CI,
3011  const int ix) {
3012  if (!CI->isLosslessCast())
3013  return false;
3014 
3015  // If this is a GC intrinsic, avoid munging types. We need types for
3016  // statepoint reconstruction in SelectionDAG.
3017  // TODO: This is probably something which should be expanded to all
3018  // intrinsics since the entire point of intrinsics is that
3019  // they are understandable by the optimizer.
3020  if (isa<GCStatepointInst>(Call) || isa<GCRelocateInst>(Call) ||
3021  isa<GCResultInst>(Call))
3022  return false;
3023 
3024  // Opaque pointers are compatible with any byval types.
3025  PointerType *SrcTy = cast<PointerType>(CI->getOperand(0)->getType());
3026  if (SrcTy->isOpaque())
3027  return true;
3028 
3029  // The size of ByVal or InAlloca arguments is derived from the type, so we
3030  // can't change to a type with a different size. If the size were
3031  // passed explicitly we could avoid this check.
3032  if (!Call.isPassPointeeByValueArgument(ix))
3033  return true;
3034 
3035  // The transform currently only handles type replacement for byval, not other
3036  // type-carrying attributes.
3037  if (!Call.isByValArgument(ix))
3038  return false;
3039 
3040  Type *SrcElemTy = SrcTy->getNonOpaquePointerElementType();
3041  Type *DstElemTy = Call.getParamByValType(ix);
3042  if (!SrcElemTy->isSized() || !DstElemTy->isSized())
3043  return false;
3044  if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(SrcElemTy) != DL.getTypeAllocSize(DstElemTy))
3045  return false;
3046  return true;
3047 }

3049 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::tryOptimizeCall(CallInst *CI) {
3050  if (!CI->getCalledFunction()) return nullptr;
3051 
3052  // Skip optimizing notail and musttail calls so
3053  // LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall doesn't have to preserve those invariants.
3054  // LibCallSimplifier::optimizeCall should try to preseve tail calls though.
3055  if (CI->isMustTailCall() || CI->isNoTailCall())
3056  return nullptr;
3057 
3058  auto InstCombineRAUW = [this](Instruction *From, Value *With) {
3059  replaceInstUsesWith(*From, With);
3060  };
3061  auto InstCombineErase = [this](Instruction *I) {
3062  eraseInstFromFunction(*I);
3063  };
3064  LibCallSimplifier Simplifier(DL, &TLI, ORE, BFI, PSI, InstCombineRAUW,
3065  InstCombineErase);
3066  if (Value *With = Simplifier.optimizeCall(CI, Builder)) {
3067  ++NumSimplified;
3068  return CI->use_empty() ? CI : replaceInstUsesWith(*CI, With);
3069  }
3070 
3071  return nullptr;
3072 }

3074 static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampolineFromAlloca(Value *TrampMem) {
3075  // Strip off at most one level of pointer casts, looking for an alloca. This
3076  // is good enough in practice and simpler than handling any number of casts.
3077  Value *Underlying = TrampMem->stripPointerCasts();
3078  if (Underlying != TrampMem &&
3079  (!Underlying->hasOneUse() || Underlying->user_back() != TrampMem))
3080  return nullptr;
3081  if (!isa<AllocaInst>(Underlying))
3082  return nullptr;
3083 
3084  IntrinsicInst *InitTrampoline = nullptr;
3085  for (User *U : TrampMem->users()) {
3086  IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(U);
3087  if (!II)
3088  return nullptr;
3089  if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::init_trampoline) {
3090  if (InitTrampoline)
3091  // More than one init_trampoline writes to this value. Give up.
3092  return nullptr;
3093  InitTrampoline = II;
3094  continue;
3095  }
3096  if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::adjust_trampoline)
3097  // Allow any number of calls to adjust.trampoline.
3098  continue;
3099  return nullptr;
3100  }
3101 
3102  // No call to init.trampoline found.
3103  if (!InitTrampoline)
3104  return nullptr;
3105 
3106  // Check that the alloca is being used in the expected way.
3107  if (InitTrampoline->getOperand(0) != TrampMem)
3108  return nullptr;
3109 
3110  return InitTrampoline;
3111 }

3113 static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampolineFromBB(IntrinsicInst *AdjustTramp,
3114  Value *TrampMem) {
3115  // Visit all the previous instructions in the basic block, and try to find a
3116  // init.trampoline which has a direct path to the adjust.trampoline.
3117  for (BasicBlock::iterator I = AdjustTramp->getIterator(),
3118  E = AdjustTramp->getParent()->begin();
3119  I != E;) {
3120  Instruction *Inst = &*--I;
3121  if (IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I))
3122  if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::init_trampoline &&
3123  II->getOperand(0) == TrampMem)
3124  return II;
3125  if (Inst->mayWriteToMemory())
3126  return nullptr;
3127  }
3128  return nullptr;
3129 }

3131 // Given a call to llvm.adjust.trampoline, find and return the corresponding
3132 // call to llvm.init.trampoline if the call to the trampoline can be optimized
3133 // to a direct call to a function. Otherwise return NULL.
3134 static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampoline(Value *Callee) {
3135  Callee = Callee->stripPointerCasts();
3136  IntrinsicInst *AdjustTramp = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Callee);
3137  if (!AdjustTramp ||
3138  AdjustTramp->getIntrinsicID() != Intrinsic::adjust_trampoline)
3139  return nullptr;
3140 
3141  Value *TrampMem = AdjustTramp->getOperand(0);
3142 
3143  if (IntrinsicInst *IT = findInitTrampolineFromAlloca(TrampMem))
3144  return IT;
3145  if (IntrinsicInst *IT = findInitTrampolineFromBB(AdjustTramp, TrampMem))
3146  return IT;
3147  return nullptr;
3148 }
