3150 bool InstCombinerImpl::annotateAnyAllocSite(CallBase &Call,
3151  const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
3152  // Note: We only handle cases which can't be driven from generic attributes
3153  // here. So, for example, nonnull and noalias (which are common properties
3154  // of some allocation functions) are expected to be handled via annotation
3155  // of the respective allocator declaration with generic attributes.
3156  bool Changed = false;
3157 
3158  if (!Call.getType()->isPointerTy())
3159  return Changed;
3160 
3161  std::optional<APInt> Size = getAllocSize(&Call, TLI);
3162  if (Size && *Size != 0) {
3163  // TODO: We really should just emit deref_or_null here and then
3164  // let the generic inference code combine that with nonnull.
3165  if (Call.hasRetAttr(Attribute::NonNull)) {
3166  Changed = !Call.hasRetAttr(Attribute::Dereferenceable);
3167  Call.addRetAttr(Attribute::getWithDereferenceableBytes(
3168  Call.getContext(), Size->getLimitedValue()));
3169  } else {
3170  Changed = !Call.hasRetAttr(Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull);
3171  Call.addRetAttr(Attribute::getWithDereferenceableOrNullBytes(
3172  Call.getContext(), Size->getLimitedValue()));
3173  }
3174  }
3175 
3176  // Add alignment attribute if alignment is a power of two constant.
3177  Value *Alignment = getAllocAlignment(&Call, TLI);
3178  if (!Alignment)
3179  return Changed;
3180 
3181  ConstantInt *AlignOpC = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Alignment);
3182  if (AlignOpC && AlignOpC->getValue().ult(llvm::Value::MaximumAlignment)) {
3183  uint64_t AlignmentVal = AlignOpC->getZExtValue();
3184  if (llvm::isPowerOf2_64(AlignmentVal)) {
3185  Align ExistingAlign = Call.getRetAlign().valueOrOne();
3186  Align NewAlign = Align(AlignmentVal);
3187  if (NewAlign > ExistingAlign) {
3188  Call.addRetAttr(
3189  Attribute::getWithAlignment(Call.getContext(), NewAlign));
3190  Changed = true;
3191  }
3192  }
3193  }
3194  return Changed;
3195 }

3197 /// Improvements for call, callbr and invoke instructions.
3198 Instruction *InstCombinerImpl::visitCallBase(CallBase &Call) {
3199  bool Changed = annotateAnyAllocSite(Call, &TLI);
3200 
3201  // Mark any parameters that are known to be non-null with the nonnull
3202  // attribute. This is helpful for inlining calls to functions with null
3203  // checks on their arguments.
3204  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> ArgNos;
3205  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
3206 
3207  for (Value *V : Call.args()) {
3208  if (V->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
3209  !Call.paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull) &&
3210  isKnownNonZero(V, DL, 0, &AC, &Call, &DT))
3211  ArgNos.push_back(ArgNo);
3212  ArgNo++;
3213  }
3214 
3215  assert(ArgNo == Call.arg_size() && "Call arguments not processed correctly.");
3216 
3217  if (!ArgNos.empty()) {
3218  AttributeList AS = Call.getAttributes();
3219  LLVMContext &Ctx = Call.getContext();
3220  AS = AS.addParamAttribute(Ctx, ArgNos,
3221  Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::NonNull));
3222  Call.setAttributes(AS);
3223  Changed = true;
3224  }
3225 
3226  // If the callee is a pointer to a function, attempt to move any casts to the
3227  // arguments of the call/callbr/invoke.
3228  Value *Callee = Call.getCalledOperand();
3229  Function *CalleeF = dyn_cast<Function>(Callee);
3230  if ((!CalleeF || CalleeF->getFunctionType() != Call.getFunctionType()) &&
3231  transformConstExprCastCall(Call))
3232  return nullptr;
3233 
3234  if (CalleeF) {
3235  // Remove the convergent attr on calls when the callee is not convergent.
3236  if (Call.isConvergent() && !CalleeF->isConvergent() &&
3237  !CalleeF->isIntrinsic()) {
3238  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing convergent attr from instr " << Call
3239  << "\n");
3240  Call.setNotConvergent();
3241  return &Call;
3242  }
3243 
3244  // If the call and callee calling conventions don't match, and neither one
3245  // of the calling conventions is compatible with C calling convention
3246  // this call must be unreachable, as the call is undefined.
3247  if ((CalleeF->getCallingConv() != Call.getCallingConv() &&
3248  !(CalleeF->getCallingConv() == llvm::CallingConv::C &&
3249  TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isCallingConvCCompatible(&Call)) &&
3250  !(Call.getCallingConv() == llvm::CallingConv::C &&
3251  TargetLibraryInfoImpl::isCallingConvCCompatible(CalleeF))) &&
3252  // Only do this for calls to a function with a body. A prototype may
3253  // not actually end up matching the implementation's calling conv for a
3254  // variety of reasons (e.g. it may be written in assembly).
3255  !CalleeF->isDeclaration()) {
3256  Instruction *OldCall = &Call;
3257  CreateNonTerminatorUnreachable(OldCall);
3258  // If OldCall does not return void then replaceInstUsesWith poison.
3259  // This allows ValueHandlers and custom metadata to adjust itself.
3260  if (!OldCall->getType()->isVoidTy())
3261  replaceInstUsesWith(*OldCall, PoisonValue::get(OldCall->getType()));
3262  if (isa<CallInst>(OldCall))
3263  return eraseInstFromFunction(*OldCall);
3264 
3265  // We cannot remove an invoke or a callbr, because it would change thexi
3266  // CFG, just change the callee to a null pointer.
3267  cast<CallBase>(OldCall)->setCalledFunction(
3268  CalleeF->getFunctionType(),
3269  Constant::getNullValue(CalleeF->getType()));
3270  return nullptr;
3271  }
3272  }
3273 
3274  // Calling a null function pointer is undefined if a null address isn't
3275  // dereferenceable.
3276  if ((isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Callee) &&
3277  !NullPointerIsDefined(Call.getFunction())) ||
3278  isa<UndefValue>(Callee)) {
3279  // If Call does not return void then replaceInstUsesWith poison.
3280  // This allows ValueHandlers and custom metadata to adjust itself.
3281  if (!Call.getType()->isVoidTy())
3282  replaceInstUsesWith(Call, PoisonValue::get(Call.getType()));
3283 
3284  if (Call.isTerminator()) {
3285  // Can't remove an invoke or callbr because we cannot change the CFG.
3286  return nullptr;
3287  }
3288 
3289  // This instruction is not reachable, just remove it.
3290  CreateNonTerminatorUnreachable(&Call);
3291  return eraseInstFromFunction(Call);
3292  }
3293 
3294  if (IntrinsicInst *II = findInitTrampoline(Callee))
3295  return transformCallThroughTrampoline(Call, *II);
3296 
3297  // TODO: Drop this transform once opaque pointer transition is done.
3298  FunctionType *FTy = Call.getFunctionType();
3299  if (FTy->isVarArg()) {
3300  int ix = FTy->getNumParams();
3301  // See if we can optimize any arguments passed through the varargs area of
3302  // the call.
3303  for (auto I = Call.arg_begin() + FTy->getNumParams(), E = Call.arg_end();
3304  I != E; ++I, ++ix) {
3305  CastInst *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(*I);
3306  if (CI && isSafeToEliminateVarargsCast(Call, DL, CI, ix)) {
3307  replaceUse(*I, CI->getOperand(0));
3308 
3309  // Update the byval type to match the pointer type.
3310  // Not necessary for opaque pointers.
3311  PointerType *NewTy = cast<PointerType>(CI->getOperand(0)->getType());
3312  if (!NewTy->isOpaque() && Call.isByValArgument(ix)) {
3313  Call.removeParamAttr(ix, Attribute::ByVal);
3314  Call.addParamAttr(ix, Attribute::getWithByValType(
3315  Call.getContext(),
3316  NewTy->getNonOpaquePointerElementType()));
3317  }
3318  Changed = true;
3319  }
3320  }
3321  }
3322 
3323  if (isa<InlineAsm>(Callee) && !Call.doesNotThrow()) {
3324  InlineAsm *IA = cast<InlineAsm>(Callee);
3325  if (!IA->canThrow()) {
3326  // Normal inline asm calls cannot throw - mark them
3327  // 'nounwind'.
3328  Call.setDoesNotThrow();
3329  Changed = true;
3330  }
3331  }
3332 
3333  // Try to optimize the call if possible, we require DataLayout for most of
3334  // this. None of these calls are seen as possibly dead so go ahead and
3335  // delete the instruction now.
3336  if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&Call)) {
3337  Instruction *I = tryOptimizeCall(CI);
3338  // If we changed something return the result, etc. Otherwise let
3339  // the fallthrough check.
3340  if (I) return eraseInstFromFunction(*I);
3341  }
3342 
3343  if (!Call.use_empty() && !Call.isMustTailCall())
3344  if (Value *ReturnedArg = Call.getReturnedArgOperand()) {
3345  Type *CallTy = Call.getType();
3346  Type *RetArgTy = ReturnedArg->getType();
3347  if (RetArgTy->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(CallTy))
3348  return replaceInstUsesWith(
3349  Call, Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(ReturnedArg, CallTy));
3350  }
3351 
3352  // Drop unnecessary kcfi operand bundles from calls that were converted
3353  // into direct calls.
3354  auto Bundle = Call.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_kcfi);
3355  if (Bundle && !Call.isIndirectCall()) {
3356  DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(DEBUG_TYPE "-kcfi", {
3357  if (CalleeF) {
3358  ConstantInt *FunctionType = nullptr;
3359  ConstantInt *ExpectedType = cast<ConstantInt>(Bundle->Inputs[0]);
3360 
3361  if (MDNode *MD = CalleeF->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_kcfi_type))
3362  FunctionType = mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(MD->getOperand(0));
3363 
3364  if (FunctionType &&
3365  FunctionType->getZExtValue() != ExpectedType->getZExtValue())
3366  dbgs() << Call.getModule()->getName()
3367  << ": warning: kcfi: " << Call.getCaller()->getName()
3368  << ": call to " << CalleeF->getName()
3369  << " using a mismatching function pointer type\n";
3370  }
3371  });
3372 
3373  return CallBase::removeOperandBundle(&Call, LLVMContext::OB_kcfi);
3374  }
3375 
3376  if (isRemovableAlloc(&Call, &TLI))
3377  return visitAllocSite(Call);
3378 
3379  // Handle intrinsics which can be used in both call and invoke context.
3380  switch (Call.getIntrinsicID()) {
3381  case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_statepoint: {
3382  GCStatepointInst &GCSP = *cast<GCStatepointInst>(&Call);
3383  SmallPtrSet<Value *, 32> LiveGcValues;
3384  for (const GCRelocateInst *Reloc : GCSP.getGCRelocates()) {
3385  GCRelocateInst &GCR = *const_cast<GCRelocateInst *>(Reloc);
3386 
3387  // Remove the relocation if unused.
3388  if (GCR.use_empty()) {
3389  eraseInstFromFunction(GCR);
3390  continue;
3391  }
3392 
3393  Value *DerivedPtr = GCR.getDerivedPtr();
3394  Value *BasePtr = GCR.getBasePtr();
3395 
3396  // Undef is undef, even after relocation.
3397  if (isa<UndefValue>(DerivedPtr) || isa<UndefValue>(BasePtr)) {
3398  replaceInstUsesWith(GCR, UndefValue::get(GCR.getType()));
3399  eraseInstFromFunction(GCR);
3400  continue;
3401  }
3402 
3403  if (auto *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(GCR.getType())) {
3404  // The relocation of null will be null for most any collector.
3405  // TODO: provide a hook for this in GCStrategy. There might be some
3406  // weird collector this property does not hold for.
3407  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(DerivedPtr)) {
3408  // Use null-pointer of gc_relocate's type to replace it.
3409  replaceInstUsesWith(GCR, ConstantPointerNull::get(PT));
3410  eraseInstFromFunction(GCR);
3411  continue;
3412  }
3413 
3414  // isKnownNonNull -> nonnull attribute
3415  if (!GCR.hasRetAttr(Attribute::NonNull) &&
3416  isKnownNonZero(DerivedPtr, DL, 0, &AC, &Call, &DT)) {
3417  GCR.addRetAttr(Attribute::NonNull);
3418  // We discovered new fact, re-check users.
3419  Worklist.pushUsersToWorkList(GCR);
3420  }
3421  }
3422 
3423  // If we have two copies of the same pointer in the statepoint argument
3424  // list, canonicalize to one. This may let us common gc.relocates.
3425  if (GCR.getBasePtr() == GCR.getDerivedPtr() &&
3426  GCR.getBasePtrIndex() != GCR.getDerivedPtrIndex()) {
3427  auto *OpIntTy = GCR.getOperand(2)->getType();
3428  GCR.setOperand(2, ConstantInt::get(OpIntTy, GCR.getBasePtrIndex()));
3429  }
3430 
3431  // TODO: bitcast(relocate(p)) -> relocate(bitcast(p))
3432  // Canonicalize on the type from the uses to the defs
3433 
3434  // TODO: relocate((gep p, C, C2, ...)) -> gep(relocate(p), C, C2, ...)
3435  LiveGcValues.insert(BasePtr);
3436  LiveGcValues.insert(DerivedPtr);
3437  }
3438  std::optional<OperandBundleUse> Bundle =
3439  GCSP.getOperandBundle(LLVMContext::OB_gc_live);
3440  unsigned NumOfGCLives = LiveGcValues.size();
3441  if (!Bundle || NumOfGCLives == Bundle->Inputs.size())
3442  break;
3443  // We can reduce the size of gc live bundle.
3444  DenseMap<Value *, unsigned> Val2Idx;
3445  std::vector<Value *> NewLiveGc;
3446  for (Value *V : Bundle->Inputs) {
3447  if (Val2Idx.count(V))
3448  continue;
3449  if (LiveGcValues.count(V)) {
3450  Val2Idx[V] = NewLiveGc.size();
3451  NewLiveGc.push_back(V);
3452  } else
3453  Val2Idx[V] = NumOfGCLives;
3454  }
3455  // Update all gc.relocates
3456  for (const GCRelocateInst *Reloc : GCSP.getGCRelocates()) {
3457  GCRelocateInst &GCR = *const_cast<GCRelocateInst *>(Reloc);
3458  Value *BasePtr = GCR.getBasePtr();
3459  assert(Val2Idx.count(BasePtr) && Val2Idx[BasePtr] != NumOfGCLives &&
3460  "Missed live gc for base pointer");
3461  auto *OpIntTy1 = GCR.getOperand(1)->getType();
3462  GCR.setOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(OpIntTy1, Val2Idx[BasePtr]));
3463  Value *DerivedPtr = GCR.getDerivedPtr();
3464  assert(Val2Idx.count(DerivedPtr) && Val2Idx[DerivedPtr] != NumOfGCLives &&
3465  "Missed live gc for derived pointer");
3466  auto *OpIntTy2 = GCR.getOperand(2)->getType();
3467  GCR.setOperand(2, ConstantInt::get(OpIntTy2, Val2Idx[DerivedPtr]));
3468  }
3469  // Create new statepoint instruction.
3470  OperandBundleDef NewBundle("gc-live", NewLiveGc);
3471  return CallBase::Create(&Call, NewBundle);
3472  }
3473  default: { break; }
3474  }
3475 
3476  return Changed ? &Call : nullptr;
3477 }

3479 /// If the callee is a constexpr cast of a function, attempt to move the cast to
3480 /// the arguments of the call/callbr/invoke.
3481 bool InstCombinerImpl::transformConstExprCastCall(CallBase &Call) {
3482  auto *Callee =
3483  dyn_cast<Function>(Call.getCalledOperand()->stripPointerCasts());
3484  if (!Callee)
3485  return false;
3486 
3487  // If this is a call to a thunk function, don't remove the cast. Thunks are
3488  // used to transparently forward all incoming parameters and outgoing return
3489  // values, so it's important to leave the cast in place.
3490  if (Callee->hasFnAttribute("thunk"))
3491  return false;
3492 
3493  // If this is a musttail call, the callee's prototype must match the caller's
3494  // prototype with the exception of pointee types. The code below doesn't
3495  // implement that, so we can't do this transform.
3496  // TODO: Do the transform if it only requires adding pointer casts.
3497  if (Call.isMustTailCall())
3498  return false;
3499 
3500  Instruction *Caller = &Call;
3501  const AttributeList &CallerPAL = Call.getAttributes();
3502 
3503  // Okay, this is a cast from a function to a different type. Unless doing so
3504  // would cause a type conversion of one of our arguments, change this call to
3505  // be a direct call with arguments casted to the appropriate types.
3506  FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
3507  Type *OldRetTy = Caller->getType();
3508  Type *NewRetTy = FT->getReturnType();
3509 
3510  // Check to see if we are changing the return type...
3511  if (OldRetTy != NewRetTy) {
3512 
3513  if (NewRetTy->isStructTy())
3514  return false; // TODO: Handle multiple return values.
3515 
3516  if (!CastInst::isBitOrNoopPointerCastable(NewRetTy, OldRetTy, DL)) {
3517  if (Callee->isDeclaration())
3518  return false; // Cannot transform this return value.
3519 
3520  if (!Caller->use_empty() &&
3521  // void -> non-void is handled specially
3522  !NewRetTy->isVoidTy())
3523  return false; // Cannot transform this return value.
3524  }
3525 
3526  if (!CallerPAL.isEmpty() && !Caller->use_empty()) {
3527  AttrBuilder RAttrs(FT->getContext(), CallerPAL.getRetAttrs());
3528  if (RAttrs.overlaps(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(NewRetTy)))
3529  return false; // Attribute not compatible with transformed value.
3530  }
3531 
3532  // If the callbase is an invoke/callbr instruction, and the return value is
3533  // used by a PHI node in a successor, we cannot change the return type of
3534  // the call because there is no place to put the cast instruction (without
3535  // breaking the critical edge). Bail out in this case.
3536  if (!Caller->use_empty()) {
3537  BasicBlock *PhisNotSupportedBlock = nullptr;
3538  if (auto *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Caller))
3539  PhisNotSupportedBlock = II->getNormalDest();
3540  if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(Caller))
3541  PhisNotSupportedBlock = CB->getDefaultDest();
3542  if (PhisNotSupportedBlock)
3543  for (User *U : Caller->users())
3544  if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(U))
3545  if (PN->getParent() == PhisNotSupportedBlock)
3546  return false;
3547  }
3548  }
3549 
3550  unsigned NumActualArgs = Call.arg_size();
3551  unsigned NumCommonArgs = std::min(FT->getNumParams(), NumActualArgs);
3552 
3553  // Prevent us turning:
3554  // declare void @takes_i32_inalloca(i32* inalloca)
3555  // call void bitcast (void (i32*)* @takes_i32_inalloca to void (i32)*)(i32 0)
3556  //
3557  // into:
3558  // call void @takes_i32_inalloca(i32* null)
3559  //
3560  // Similarly, avoid folding away bitcasts of byval calls.
3561  if (Callee->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::InAlloca) ||
3562  Callee->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Preallocated))
3563  return false;
3564 
3565  auto AI = Call.arg_begin();
3566  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumCommonArgs; i != e; ++i, ++AI) {
3567  Type *ParamTy = FT->getParamType(i);
3568  Type *ActTy = (*AI)->getType();
3569 
3570  if (!CastInst::isBitOrNoopPointerCastable(ActTy, ParamTy, DL))
3571  return false; // Cannot transform this parameter value.
3572 
3573  // Check if there are any incompatible attributes we cannot drop safely.
3574  if (AttrBuilder(FT->getContext(), CallerPAL.getParamAttrs(i))
3575  .overlaps(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(
3576  ParamTy, AttributeFuncs::ASK_UNSAFE_TO_DROP)))
3577  return false; // Attribute not compatible with transformed value.
3578 
3579  if (Call.isInAllocaArgument(i) ||
3580  CallerPAL.hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::Preallocated))
3581  return false; // Cannot transform to and from inalloca/preallocated.
3582 
3583  if (CallerPAL.hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::SwiftError))
3584  return false;
3585 
3586  if (CallerPAL.hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal) !=
3587  Callee->getAttributes().hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal))
3588  return false; // Cannot transform to or from byval.
3589 
3590  // If the parameter is passed as a byval argument, then we have to have a
3591  // sized type and the sized type has to have the same size as the old type.
3592  if (ParamTy != ActTy && CallerPAL.hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal)) {
3593  PointerType *ParamPTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(ParamTy);
3594  if (!ParamPTy)
3595  return false;
3596 
3597  if (!ParamPTy->isOpaque()) {
3598  Type *ParamElTy = ParamPTy->getNonOpaquePointerElementType();
3599  if (!ParamElTy->isSized())
3600  return false;
3601 
3602  Type *CurElTy = Call.getParamByValType(i);
3603  if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(CurElTy) != DL.getTypeAllocSize(ParamElTy))
3604  return false;
3605  }
3606  }
3607  }
3608 
3609  if (Callee->isDeclaration()) {
3610  // Do not delete arguments unless we have a function body.
3611  if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs && !FT->isVarArg())
3612  return false;
3613 
3614  // If the callee is just a declaration, don't change the varargsness of the
3615  // call. We don't want to introduce a varargs call where one doesn't
3616  // already exist.
3617  if (FT->isVarArg() != Call.getFunctionType()->isVarArg())
3618  return false;
3619 
3620  // If both the callee and the cast type are varargs, we still have to make
3621  // sure the number of fixed parameters are the same or we have the same
3622  // ABI issues as if we introduce a varargs call.
3623  if (FT->isVarArg() && Call.getFunctionType()->isVarArg() &&
3624  FT->getNumParams() != Call.getFunctionType()->getNumParams())
3625  return false;
3626  }
3627 
3628  if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs && FT->isVarArg() &&
3629  !CallerPAL.isEmpty()) {
3630  // In this case we have more arguments than the new function type, but we
3631  // won't be dropping them. Check that these extra arguments have attributes
3632  // that are compatible with being a vararg call argument.
3633  unsigned SRetIdx;
3634  if (CallerPAL.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::StructRet, &SRetIdx) &&
3635  SRetIdx - AttributeList::FirstArgIndex >= FT->getNumParams())
3636  return false;
3637  }
3638 
3639  // Okay, we decided that this is a safe thing to do: go ahead and start
3640  // inserting cast instructions as necessary.
3641  SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args;
3642  SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> ArgAttrs;
3643  Args.reserve(NumActualArgs);
3644  ArgAttrs.reserve(NumActualArgs);
3645 
3646  // Get any return attributes.
3647  AttrBuilder RAttrs(FT->getContext(), CallerPAL.getRetAttrs());
3648 
3649  // If the return value is not being used, the type may not be compatible
3650  // with the existing attributes. Wipe out any problematic attributes.
3651  RAttrs.remove(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(NewRetTy));
3652 
3653  LLVMContext &Ctx = Call.getContext();
3654  AI = Call.arg_begin();
3655  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumCommonArgs; ++i, ++AI) {
3656  Type *ParamTy = FT->getParamType(i);
3657 
3658  Value *NewArg = *AI;
3659  if ((*AI)->getType() != ParamTy)
3660  NewArg = Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(*AI, ParamTy);
3661  Args.push_back(NewArg);
3662 
3663  // Add any parameter attributes except the ones incompatible with the new
3664  // type. Note that we made sure all incompatible ones are safe to drop.
3665  AttributeMask IncompatibleAttrs = AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(
3666  ParamTy, AttributeFuncs::ASK_SAFE_TO_DROP);
3667  if (CallerPAL.hasParamAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal) &&
3668  !ParamTy->isOpaquePointerTy()) {
3669  AttrBuilder AB(Ctx, CallerPAL.getParamAttrs(i).removeAttributes(
3670  Ctx, IncompatibleAttrs));
3671  AB.addByValAttr(ParamTy->getNonOpaquePointerElementType());
3672  ArgAttrs.push_back(AttributeSet::get(Ctx, AB));
3673  } else {
3674  ArgAttrs.push_back(
3675  CallerPAL.getParamAttrs(i).removeAttributes(Ctx, IncompatibleAttrs));
3676  }
3677  }
3678 
3679  // If the function takes more arguments than the call was taking, add them
3680  // now.
3681  for (unsigned i = NumCommonArgs; i != FT->getNumParams(); ++i) {
3682  Args.push_back(Constant::getNullValue(FT->getParamType(i)));
3683  ArgAttrs.push_back(AttributeSet());
3684  }
3685 
3686  // If we are removing arguments to the function, emit an obnoxious warning.
3687  if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs) {
3688  // TODO: if (!FT->isVarArg()) this call may be unreachable. PR14722
3689  if (FT->isVarArg()) {
3690  // Add all of the arguments in their promoted form to the arg list.
3691  for (unsigned i = FT->getNumParams(); i != NumActualArgs; ++i, ++AI) {
3692  Type *PTy = getPromotedType((*AI)->getType());
3693  Value *NewArg = *AI;
3694  if (PTy != (*AI)->getType()) {
3695  // Must promote to pass through va_arg area!
3696  Instruction::CastOps opcode =
3697  CastInst::getCastOpcode(*AI, false, PTy, false);
3698  NewArg = Builder.CreateCast(opcode, *AI, PTy);
3699  }
3700  Args.push_back(NewArg);
3701 
3702  // Add any parameter attributes.
3703  ArgAttrs.push_back(CallerPAL.getParamAttrs(i));
3704  }
3705  }
3706  }
3707 
3708  AttributeSet FnAttrs = CallerPAL.getFnAttrs();
3709 
3710  if (NewRetTy->isVoidTy())
3711  Caller->setName(""); // Void type should not have a name.
3712 
3713  assert((ArgAttrs.size() == FT->getNumParams() || FT->isVarArg()) &&
3714  "missing argument attributes");
3715  AttributeList NewCallerPAL = AttributeList::get(
3716  Ctx, FnAttrs, AttributeSet::get(Ctx, RAttrs), ArgAttrs);
3717 
3718  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
3719  Call.getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
3720 
3721  CallBase *NewCall;
3722  if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Caller)) {
3723  NewCall = Builder.CreateInvoke(Callee, II->getNormalDest(),
3724  II->getUnwindDest(), Args, OpBundles);
3725  } else if (CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(Caller)) {
3726  NewCall = Builder.CreateCallBr(Callee, CBI->getDefaultDest(),
3727  CBI->getIndirectDests(), Args, OpBundles);
3728  } else {
3729  NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args, OpBundles);
3730  cast<CallInst>(NewCall)->setTailCallKind(
3731  cast<CallInst>(Caller)->getTailCallKind());
3732  }
3733  NewCall->takeName(Caller);
3734  NewCall->setCallingConv(Call.getCallingConv());
3735  NewCall->setAttributes(NewCallerPAL);
3736 
3737  // Preserve prof metadata if any.
3738  NewCall->copyMetadata(*Caller, {LLVMContext::MD_prof});
3739 
3740  // Insert a cast of the return type as necessary.
3741  Instruction *NC = NewCall;
3742  Value *NV = NC;
3743  if (OldRetTy != NV->getType() && !Caller->use_empty()) {
3744  if (!NV->getType()->isVoidTy()) {
3745  NV = NC = CastInst::CreateBitOrPointerCast(NC, OldRetTy);
3746  NC->setDebugLoc(Caller->getDebugLoc());
3747 
3748  Instruction *InsertPt = NewCall->getInsertionPointAfterDef();
3749  assert(InsertPt && "No place to insert cast");
3750  InsertNewInstBefore(NC, *InsertPt);
3751  Worklist.pushUsersToWorkList(*Caller);
3752  } else {
3753  NV = PoisonValue::get(Caller->getType());
3754  }
3755  }
3756 
3757  if (!Caller->use_empty())
3758  replaceInstUsesWith(*Caller, NV);
3759  else if (Caller->hasValueHandle()) {
3760  if (OldRetTy == NV->getType())
3761  ValueHandleBase::ValueIsRAUWd(Caller, NV);
3762  else
3763  // We cannot call ValueIsRAUWd with a different type, and the
3764  // actual tracked value will disappear.
3765  ValueHandleBase::ValueIsDeleted(Caller);
3766  }
3767 
3768  eraseInstFromFunction(*Caller);
3769  return true;
3770 }
3771 
3772 /// Turn a call to a function created by init_trampoline / adjust_trampoline
3773 /// intrinsic pair into a direct call to the underlying function.
3774 Instruction *
3775 InstCombinerImpl::transformCallThroughTrampoline(CallBase &Call,
3776  IntrinsicInst &Tramp) {
3777  Value *Callee = Call.getCalledOperand();
3778  Type *CalleeTy = Callee->getType();
3779  FunctionType *FTy = Call.getFunctionType();
3780  AttributeList Attrs = Call.getAttributes();
3781 
3782  // If the call already has the 'nest' attribute somewhere then give up -
3783  // otherwise 'nest' would occur twice after splicing in the chain.
3784  if (Attrs.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Nest))
3785  return nullptr;
3786 
3787  Function *NestF = cast<Function>(Tramp.getArgOperand(1)->stripPointerCasts());
3788  FunctionType *NestFTy = NestF->getFunctionType();
3789 
3790  AttributeList NestAttrs = NestF->getAttributes();
3791  if (!NestAttrs.isEmpty()) {
3792  unsigned NestArgNo = 0;
3793  Type *NestTy = nullptr;
3794  AttributeSet NestAttr;
3795 
3796  // Look for a parameter marked with the 'nest' attribute.
3797  for (FunctionType::param_iterator I = NestFTy->param_begin(),
3798  E = NestFTy->param_end();
3799  I != E; ++NestArgNo, ++I) {
3800  AttributeSet AS = NestAttrs.getParamAttrs(NestArgNo);
3801  if (AS.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest)) {
3802  // Record the parameter type and any other attributes.
3803  NestTy = *I;
3804  NestAttr = AS;
3805  break;
3806  }
3807  }
3808 
3809  if (NestTy) {
3810  std::vector<Value*> NewArgs;
3811  std::vector<AttributeSet> NewArgAttrs;
3812  NewArgs.reserve(Call.arg_size() + 1);
3813  NewArgAttrs.reserve(Call.arg_size());
3814 
3815  // Insert the nest argument into the call argument list, which may
3816  // mean appending it. Likewise for attributes.
3817 
3818  {
3819  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
3820  auto I = Call.arg_begin(), E = Call.arg_end();
3821  do {
3822  if (ArgNo == NestArgNo) {
3823  // Add the chain argument and attributes.
3824  Value *NestVal = Tramp.getArgOperand(2);
3825  if (NestVal->getType() != NestTy)
3826  NestVal = Builder.CreateBitCast(NestVal, NestTy, "nest");
3827  NewArgs.push_back(NestVal);
3828  NewArgAttrs.push_back(NestAttr);
3829  }
3830 
3831  if (I == E)
3832  break;
3833 
3834  // Add the original argument and attributes.
3835  NewArgs.push_back(*I);
3836  NewArgAttrs.push_back(Attrs.getParamAttrs(ArgNo));
3837 
3838  ++ArgNo;
3839  ++I;
3840  } while (true);
3841  }
3842 
3843  // The trampoline may have been bitcast to a bogus type (FTy).
3844  // Handle this by synthesizing a new function type, equal to FTy
3845  // with the chain parameter inserted.
3846 
3847  std::vector<Type*> NewTypes;
3848  NewTypes.reserve(FTy->getNumParams()+1);
3849 
3850  // Insert the chain's type into the list of parameter types, which may
3851  // mean appending it.
3852  {
3853  unsigned ArgNo = 0;
3854  FunctionType::param_iterator I = FTy->param_begin(),
3855  E = FTy->param_end();
3856 
3857  do {
3858  if (ArgNo == NestArgNo)
3859  // Add the chain's type.
3860  NewTypes.push_back(NestTy);
3861 
3862  if (I == E)
3863  break;
3864 
3865  // Add the original type.
3866  NewTypes.push_back(*I);
3867 
3868  ++ArgNo;
3869  ++I;
3870  } while (true);
3871  }
3872 
3873  // Replace the trampoline call with a direct call. Let the generic
3874  // code sort out any function type mismatches.
3875  FunctionType *NewFTy = FunctionType::get(FTy->getReturnType(), NewTypes,
3876  FTy->isVarArg());
3877  Constant *NewCallee =
3878  NestF->getType() == PointerType::getUnqual(NewFTy) ?
3879  NestF : ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NestF,
3880  PointerType::getUnqual(NewFTy));
3881  AttributeList NewPAL =
3882  AttributeList::get(FTy->getContext(), Attrs.getFnAttrs(),
3883  Attrs.getRetAttrs(), NewArgAttrs);
3884 
3885  SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
3886  Call.getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
3887 
3888  Instruction *NewCaller;
3889  if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&Call)) {
3890  NewCaller = InvokeInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee,
3891  II->getNormalDest(), II->getUnwindDest(),
3892  NewArgs, OpBundles);
3893  cast<InvokeInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(II->getCallingConv());
3894  cast<InvokeInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
3895  } else if (CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(&Call)) {
3896  NewCaller =
3897  CallBrInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee, CBI->getDefaultDest(),
3898  CBI->getIndirectDests(), NewArgs, OpBundles);
3899  cast<CallBrInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(CBI->getCallingConv());
3900  cast<CallBrInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
3901  } else {
3902  NewCaller = CallInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee, NewArgs, OpBundles);
3903  cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setTailCallKind(
3904  cast<CallInst>(Call).getTailCallKind());
3905  cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(
3906  cast<CallInst>(Call).getCallingConv());
3907  cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
3908  }
3909  NewCaller->setDebugLoc(Call.getDebugLoc());
3910 
3911  return NewCaller;
3912  }
3913  }
3914 
3915  // Replace the trampoline call with a direct call. Since there is no 'nest'
3916  // parameter, there is no need to adjust the argument list. Let the generic
3917  // code sort out any function type mismatches.
3918  Constant *NewCallee = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NestF, CalleeTy);
3919  Call.setCalledFunction(FTy, NewCallee);
3920  return &Call;
3921 }
